&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;h3 style="margin: 0in;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; color: black;"&gt;ABOUT OPORTUN&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"&gt;Oportun (Nasdaq: OPRT) is a digital banking platform that puts its 1.9 million members' financial goals within reach. With intelligent borrowing, savings, budgeting, and spending capabilities, Oportun empowers members with the confidence to build a better financial future. Since inception, Oportun has provided more than $15.5 billion in responsible and affordable credit, saved its members more than $2.3 billion in interest and fees, and helped our members save an average of more than $1,800 annually. For more information, visit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="http://oportun.com/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="http://Oportun.com" data-sk="tooltip_parent"&gt;Oportun.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; color: black;"&gt;WORKING AT OPORTUN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;Working at Oportun means enjoying a differentiated experience of being part of a team that fosters a diverse, equitable and inclusive culture where we all feel a sense of belonging and are encouraged to share our perspectives. This inclusive culture is directly connected to our organization's performance and ability to fulfill our mission of delivering affordable credit to those left out of the financial mainstream. We celebrate and nurture our inclusive culture through our employee resource groups.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div class="page"&gt;
&lt;div class="layoutArea"&gt;
&lt;div class="column"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a passionate, skilled, and creative problem solver to join the team as &lt;strong&gt;Senior Product Design Manager&lt;/strong&gt; for Oportun, working to accelerating growth across our products. You will design how our members interact with their finances, helping them create a path to financial health, and improve their financial lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft best-in-class digital experiences for our members, across a suite of native and web apps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver impactful end-to-end solutions that solve member problems and move business metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion design quality, attention to detail and focus on impact while designing experiences that best support our members financial health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dive deeply into complex problem and product spaces to better understand what we are building, who we are building for and how to support designers in their work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage designers through feedback and collaborative working sessions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a culture of career growth for designers through goal setting and regular check-ins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure team members gain fluency in the methods of product design, and are able to support their projects in all phases from ideation through prototyping, user testing, and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and iterate on our discovery process to ensure we’re solving the right problems with the right solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and iterate on delivery process to improve delivery quality and speed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to our design system, to ensure product quality and consistency across the member experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quickly iterate to deliver innovative experiences that meet and exceed business goals and objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to bring teams closer and improve collaboration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for design quality and lead design QA efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cross-functional leaders to set vision, define strategy, set quarterly goals, and build roadmaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;REQUIREMENTS:&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Typically requires a &lt;strong&gt;minimum of 8 years of related experience&lt;/strong&gt; with a Bachelor’s degree or an equivalent combination of education and experience. With a minimum of &lt;strong&gt;4 years of experience directly managing product designers working on iOS/Android and web applications.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading efforts to build and improve the culture of teams and cross-functional partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly empathic manager who leads with compassion and is able to influence partners and teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert in design thinking, product research, user analysis, ideation, design, testing, and validation for highly complex work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to make sense of complex, high quantity, and sometimes contradictory information to effectively solve problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills, both written and verbal, to influence thinking and decision making with teams, stakeholders, and cross-functional partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compassion for our members and the importance of making financial health accessible by anyone, especially those who need it most.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expertise with Figma (mandatory)&lt;/strong&gt; and all aspects of the mobile and web product lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as an essential partner in a working team with product managers and engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating design solutions within the financial technology space preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and consider all qualified applicants for employment opportunities without regard to race, age, color, religion, gender, national origin, disability, sexual orientation, veteran status or any other category protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we operate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;California applicants can find a copy of Oportun's CCPA Notice here:&amp;nbsp; &lt;a href="https://oportun.com/privacy/california-privacy-notice/"&gt;https://oportun.com/privacy/california-privacy-notice/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin: 0in; text-align: justify;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"&gt;We will never request personal identifiable information (bank, credit card, etc.) before you are hired. We do not charge you for pre-employment fees such as background checks, training, or equipment. If you think you have been a victim of fraud by someone posing as us, please report your experience to the FBI’s Internet Crime Complaint Center (IC3).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;At Coinbase, our mission is to&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://blog.coinbase.com/our-mission-strategy-and-culture-18a92a3bb0fa"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;increase economic freedom around the world&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;, and we couldn’t do this without hiring the best people. We’re a group of hard-working overachievers who are deeply focused on building the future of finance and Web3 for our users across the globe, whether they’re trading, storing, staking or using crypto. Know those people who always lead the group project? That’s us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;There are a few things we look for across all hires we make at Coinbase, regardless of role or team. First, we look for candidates who will thrive in a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://blog.coinbase.com/culture-at-coinbase-f0e1c2a99aff"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;culture&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; like ours, where we default to trust, embrace feedback, and disrupt ourselves. Second, we expect all employees to commit to our&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://blog.coinbase.com/coinbase-is-a-mission-focused-company-af882df8804"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;mission-focused approach&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; to our work. Finally, we seek people who are excited to learn about and live crypto, because those are the folks who enjoy the intense moments in our sprint and recharge work culture. We’re a remote-first company looking to hire the absolute best talent all over the world.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to #LiveCrypto? Who you are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;You’ve got positive energy. You’re optimistic about the future and determined to get there.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;You’re never tired of learning. You want to be a pro in bleeding edge tech like DeFi, NFTs, DAOs, and Web 3.0.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;You appreciate direct communication. You’re both an active communicator and an eager listener - because let’s face it, you can’t have one without the other. You’re cool with candid feedback and see every setback as an opportunity to grow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;You can pivot on the fly. Crypto is constantly evolving, so our priorities do, too. What you worked on last month may not be what you work on today, and that excites you. You’re not looking for a boring job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;You have a “can do” attitude. Our teams create high-quality work on quick timelines. Owning a problem doesn’t scare you, but rather empowers you to take 100% responsibility for achieving our mission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;You want to be part of a winning team. We’re stronger together, and you’re a person who embraces being pushed out of your comfort zone. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Advanced Design and Research team at Coinbase plays a critical role in executing on our vision to create more economic freedom for the world. We’re building the most secure, trusted, and intuitive to use cryptocurrency products for advanced traders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing (ie. job duties):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; To be completed by all business teams except Eng.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a small team to iteratively improve user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take new features from ideation, to prototyping, to user testing, to production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design web and mobile experiences that are simple and intuitive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with our Design Systems team to document and define scalable design patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in regular design reviews where you’ll seek out specific feedback on your designs and incorporate relevant feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute on the product roadmap and help define product strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Daily collaboration with Engineering, User Research, and Product&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for in you (ie. job requirements):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; To be completed by all business teams except Eng.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional Product Design experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor's degree in a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing consumer-facing experiences for web and mobile&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellence in UX thinking, visual design, and written communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a collaborative environment with engineers, user researchers, and product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in Figma and prototyping tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Low ego, collaborative, and open minded&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in crypto or financial products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User of Coinbase products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User of advanced trading tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class="content-pay-transparency"&gt;&lt;div class="pay-input"&gt;&lt;div class="description"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Transparency Notice:&lt;/strong&gt; Depending on your work location, the target annual salary for this position can range as detailed below. Full time offers from Coinbase also include &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;target bonus + target equity + benefits (including medical, dental, vision and 401(k)).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="title"&gt;Pay Range: &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="pay-range"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$175,100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="divider"&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$206,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Commitment to Equal Opportunity&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer.&amp;nbsp; All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, sex, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation or any other basis protected by applicable law. Coinbase will also consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. &amp;nbsp;For US applicants, you may view&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://www.dol.gov/sites/dolgov/files/ofccp/pdf/pay-transp_English_unformattedESQA508c.pdf" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://www.dol.gov/sites/dolgov/files/ofccp/pdf/pay-transp_English_unformattedESQA508c.pdf" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;Pay Transparency&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://www.dol.gov/sites/dolgov/files/WHD/legacy/files/eppac.pdf" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://www.dol.gov/sites/dolgov/files/WHD/legacy/files/eppac.pdf" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;Employee Rights&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://www.eeoc.gov/sites/default/files/2022-10/22-088_EEOC_KnowYourRights_10_20.pdf" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://www.eeoc.gov/sites/default/files/2022-10/22-088_EEOC_KnowYourRights_10_20.pdf" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;Know Your Rights&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;notices by clicking on their corresponding links.&amp;nbsp; Additionally, Coinbase participates in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://static-assets.coinbase.com/e-verify.pdf" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://static-assets.coinbase.com/e-verify.pdf" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;E-Verify program&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;in certain locations, as required by law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Coinbase is also committed to providing reasonable accommodations to individuals with disabilities. If you need a reasonable accommodation because of a disability for any part of the employment process, please send an e-mail to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;accommodations[at]coinbase.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; and let us know the nature of your request and your contact information.&amp;nbsp; For quick access to screen reading technology compatible with this site &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/chromevox/kgejglhpjiefppelpmljglcjbhoiplfn"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;click here to download&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; a free compatible screen reader &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.chromevox.com/tutorial/"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;(free step by step tutorial can be found here)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Global Data Privacy Notice for Job Candidates and Applicants&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Depending on your location, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) may regulate the way we manage the data of job applicants. Our full notice outlining how data will be processed as part of the application procedure for applicable locations is available &lt;a href="https://www.coinbase.com/legal/applicant_privacy_notice" target="_blank"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;By submitting your application, you are agreeing to our use and processing of your data as required. For US applicants only, by submitting your application you are agreeing to arbitration of disputes as outlined &lt;a href="https://www.coinbase.com/legal/application-arbitration-agreement"&gt;here.&lt;/a&gt; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Altera, a new member of the N. Harris Computer Corporation family, delivers health IT solutions that support caregivers around the world. These include the Sunrise™, Paragon®, Altera TouchWorks®, Altera Opal, STAR™, HealthQuest™ and dbMotion™ solutions. At the intersection of technology and the human experience, Altera Digital Health is driving a new era of healthcare, in which innovation and expertise can elevate care delivery and inspire healthier communities across the globe. A new age in healthcare technology has just begun.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Chief Information Officer will have responsibility for all IT Operations and Strategic planning for a client hospital system.&amp;nbsp; The system includes multiple hospitals, emergency departments and clinics covering acute and ambulatory clinical services in the southwest region of the US.&amp;nbsp; Responsibilities include day to day service delivery, planning, coordination of healthcare IT programs, gathering requirements and planning for systems selection, system design, testing, implementation, systems integration, training and system maintenance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be an integral leadership position within the client organization that is dedicated to the high quality patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and manage information technology strategic plans, programs, and schedules for business and finance data processing, computer services, network communications, and management information services to accomplish corporate goals and objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ability to collaborate with individual contributors and business leaders to define business process issues, operational efficiencies, implement creative solutions, and measure delivery results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of corporate environment and business metrics, with ability to propose solutions for achievement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage profitability and margin contribution for client account within managed services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective and efficient IT services which meet the needs of client hospital and/or physician group.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Account profitability which meet revenue and margin requirements set at the corporate level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective management of the client relationship and resolution of client issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous risk management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for the development and review of all back-up and disaster recovery procedures and plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective utilization and management of staff such that milestones/goals are obtained and staff is motivated and competent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify emerging information technologies to be assimilated, integrated, and introduced within the client account.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safeguard technology deployments are properly implemented, integrated and supported.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational accountability for change management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the security of the information systems, communication lines, and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate client service and support with the software engineering process to support timely resolution of client issues and improve application usability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and recruit internal/external talents to ensure effective mix of competencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Induct new joiners in order to quickly maximize performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and communicate team/individual objectives and KPI to inspire individuals to achieve high performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Allocate work load to fully utilize every employee’s talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement development plans and coach for individuals to reach their maximum talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide regular constructive feedback on performance/development and address poor/mediocre performance on a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognize high performers to maintain motivation and retain key talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regularly communicate on company news and team progress against business plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create team spirit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems or other technology-related field or relevant business/information technology experience&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Preferred&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced degree in information technology and/or healthcare preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work Experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;15+ Years in IT management preferred&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7+ years relevant leadership experience including responsibility for organizational objectives and measurements preferred&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge, Skills and Abilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standard work week or as defined by assignment requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primarily works in standard office environment or remotely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;May require after-hours, on-call support and/or holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On-call and after hours work during peak times including end of month/quarter/year; during this time PTO is limited to meet business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to 10% travel may be required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Altera is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. We consider applicants without regard to race, color, religion, age, national origin, ancestry, ethnicity, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, marital status, veteran status, disability, genetic information, citizenship status, or membership in any other group protected by federal, state or local law.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you would like to contact us regarding the accessibility of our website or need assistance completing the application process, please contact us at:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:HR.Recruiting@alteraehealth.com"&gt;HR.Recruiting@AlteraHealth.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.alterahealth.com/legal/privacy-policy/"&gt;https://www.alterahealth.com/legal/privacy-policy/&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Altera, a new member of the N. Harris Computer Corporation family, delivers health IT solutions that support caregivers around the world. These include the Sunrise™, Paragon®, Altera TouchWorks®, Altera Opal, STAR™, HealthQuest™ and dbMotion™ solutions. At the intersection of technology and the human experience, Altera Digital Health is driving a new era of healthcare, in which innovation and expertise can elevate care delivery and inspire healthier communities across the globe. A new age in healthcare technology has just begun.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provides support, maintenance, and monitoring of the corporate network infrastructure including hardware and related protocols. Processes network infrastructure requests and serves as an escalation point for networking issues that cannot be resolved by junior associates and independently troubleshoots major incidents. Owns, plans, executes, and documents complex technical projects from concept to completion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The position is mostly remote but the individual needs to be within an hour commute from the Raleigh/Durham, NC metro area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configures, maintains, and operates routers, switches, firewalls, wireless access points, load balancers, VOIP equipment, and monitoring tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installs physical equipment, connects cabling, dresses communications racks, powers devices per provided documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversees the proactive monitoring of the network infrastructure via monitoring tools, addresses alerts in a timely manner, and documents topologies and changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentors, coaches, and knowledge shares with junior associates and peers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Is the escalation point for junior associates handling difficult incidents/requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently processes routine requests for network services, access, and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently troubleshoots and resolves major incidents, runs outage bridges, and seeks root cause analysis for complex network issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently owns network infrastructure projects from concept to completion including requirements gathering, implementation, turn up, testing, and hand off of the technology solution to the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently becomes a subject matter expert in one or more network specialty domain such as datacenter, firewall, wireless, load balancing, cloud networking, or VOIP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributes to the implementation of major network infrastructure projects in cooperation with senior engineers and peers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Academic and Professional Qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent/years of experience required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desired certifications: Cisco Certified Technician (CCT), Cisco Certified Network Engineer (CCNA), Cisco Certified Network Professional (CCNP), ITIL Foundations, Security+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-7 years relevant work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work collaboratively with a team and receive constructive feedback from senior engineers and leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to provide excellent customer service when working directly with users that may not be technical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to provide mentoring, coaching, and knowledge sharing in a constructive manner to junior associates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to own a project from concept to completion including requirements gathering, documentation, implementation, testing, turn up, and hand over&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to become subject matter expert in one or more network specialty domain: firewalls, VOIP, datacenter technologies, load balancers, cloud networking, wireless, packet analysis, networking tools (DNAC, PRTG, ISE, etc.), low voltage design, MPLS, or route/switch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of TCP/IP Protocol Stack (This would cover IP Addressing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding and past or present experience configuring and troubleshooting OSPF, EIGRP and BGP routing protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of Layer 2 switching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Very strong knowledge of vendor management, equipment (Cisco, Aruba, Arista), and working with ISPs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Very strong knowledge of hardware installation, low voltage cabling standards, power and data cable management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of wireless networking, firewalls, VOIP, datacenter technologies, load balancers, or cloud networking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Travel Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On-site support for local office and/or local data center may be required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to 10% travel may be required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;International travel may be required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working Arrangements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standard work week or as defined by assignment requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primarily works in a remote environment but is assigned to local office location&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;May require after-hours, on-call support and/or holidays per on-call rotation or as defined by assignment requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On-call and after hours work during peak times including end of month/quarter/year; during this time PTO may be limited to meet business needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
