&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Altera, a new member of the N. Harris Computer Corporation family, delivers health IT solutions that support caregivers around the world. These include the Sunrise™, Paragon®, Altera TouchWorks®, Altera Opal, STAR™, HealthQuest™ and dbMotion™ solutions. At the intersection of technology and the human experience, Altera Digital Health is driving a new era of healthcare, in which innovation and expertise can elevate care delivery and inspire healthier communities across the globe. A new age in healthcare technology has just begun.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***FINANCIAL DATA ANALYST***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Remote Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Financial Data Analyst is a key member of our finance team, responsible for collecting, analyzing, and reporting on financial data. This includes using your understanding of data and business intelligence to identify trends, patterns, and insights that can help our business units make informed decisions. You’ll also play a critical role in supporting Altera by providing timely information to internal and external clients. Your clients will range from an auditor to an EVP!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with business units to understand their data needs and develop data-driven solutions to their challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and analyze financial data from a variety of sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use advanced Excel skills and data visualization tools to create and deliver reports and presentations that clearly communicate financial data and insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify trends, patterns, and insights in financial data and develop recommendations for business improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams to develop and implement data-driven strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date on the latest financial data analysis tools and techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to internal and external audit requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide timely, accurate information to internal and external clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Education&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor’s degree in finance, accounting, business administration, or a related field, or equivalent years of experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Work Experience &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years’ experience in financial data analysis; accounts receivables experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read, analyze and interpret contracts, reconciliations and other company documents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong work ethic and self-starter, able to effectively manage multiple priorities and adapt to change within a fast-paced business environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent listening skills and the ability to ask probing questions, understand concerns, and overcome objections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must possess and be able to demonstrate strong influencing and resolution skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills; excellent communication and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel skills, including macros, pivot tables, and VLOOKUPs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with Power BI and other data analysis tools preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with cross-functional teams; able to work independently and as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of contract language; experience handling contract disputes and negotiating with clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to de-escalate and manage difficult conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHY JOIN US?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll come to have a broad understanding of our business, the needs of our clients, and the latest financial data analysis tools and techniques. We offer a collaborative and supportive work environment where you can learn from and lean on your colleagues. We are committed to helping you grow and develop your career. Altera is a dynamic company with high expectations, but we also offer great flexibility, including the ability to work remotely.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a talented and motivated Financial Data Analyst who is looking for a challenging and rewarding role where you can make a real impact on the success of Altera and its clients, we encourage you to apply!&lt;/p&gt;
