&lt;li&gt;Clearly articulate the vision to the team. Build relationships and work effectively with people at all levels of the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage team workload and ensure deadlines are met. Fill in business analyst gaps as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the team to other departments and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION &amp;amp; WORK EXPERIENCE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Education&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in business, IT, Marketing, Finance, or business-related field, or equivalent years of experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MBA preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Work Experience&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years product management / business analyst work experience; 2-3 years at the expert/principal business analyst level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert level experience in providing business process support for a healthcare IT solution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years formal or informal team leadership; experienced in bringing people together to create and execute a plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced at providing clear communications and directives to a team; skilled in conflict resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in tracking and managing numerous complex details simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of our Sunrise solution preferred, or knowledgeable of other EHR solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3 years’ experience with SAFe or Agile processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 – 3 years demonstrated success in revenue generation, product management, and/or partnership development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in analyzing market gaps; able to recommend stages of product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to lead design forums and requirements gathering workshops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced at interacting with customers, partners, market consultants to address market-product competition mix; able to translate customer problems into features and design requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of innovating product-based solutions based on changing market and customer requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WORK ARRANGEMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remote U.S. or Canada-based role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TRAVEL &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Up to 25% may be required.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Altera is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. We consider applicants without regard to race, color, religion, age, national origin, ancestry, ethnicity, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, marital status, veteran status, disability, genetic information, citizenship status, or membership in any other group protected by federal, state or local law.&lt;/p&gt;
