&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Brex empowers the next generation of businesses with an integrated corporate card and spend management software. We make it easy for our customers to manage every aspect of spending and empower their employees to make better financial decisions from anywhere they live or work. Brex proudly serves tens of thousands of growing businesses, from early-stage startups to enterprise leaders.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Working at Brex allows you to push your limits, challenge the status quo, and collaborate with some of the brightest minds in the industry. We’re committed to building a diverse team and inclusive culture and believe your potential should only be limited by how big you can dream. We make this a reality by empowering you with the tools, resources, and support you need to grow your career.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engineering at Brex&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;The Engineering team includes Data, IT, Security, and Software, and is responsible for building innovative products and infrastructure for Brex and our customers. We believe that engineers should accelerate the business through technology, and collaborate across multiple teams to accomplish that.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Teams are autonomous, value inclusivity, eager to learn, teach and constantly improve how things work. The software we build today is the foundation for dozens of Brex systems in the future, so engineers have a strong sense of ownership and accountability and take pride in their craft.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;As an engineer on the core languages team you will be defining how Kotlin and graphQL are written at Brex. Work you will do will impact every backend developer at Brex. You will be writing libraries, and abstractions to empower all of Brex Engineering.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;You'll have the opportunity to learn and push the frontier of providing the best financial software experience to help companies grow. You’ll be encouraged to be metric and data-driven and to think creatively to help Brex scale and get prepared for the new markets we are about to enter.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Write and maintain libraries for Kotlin and graphQL.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Working on identifying reliability and performance improvements on our backend stack (grpc and graphQL)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Deep functional expertise in Kotlin and graphQL to understand and debug Brex eng wide problems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Apply functional expertise in Kotlin and graphQL to understand and debug brex eng wide problems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Define best practices around Kotlin and graphQL on how code should be written&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;5+ years of professional experience in a software engineering role or equivalent experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Experience building and designing scalable backend systems&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Experience working with SQL or NoSQL databases&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Experience working with Kotlin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Familiarity with software engineering development cycles&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Ability to hold yourself and the team to high standards&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Experience collaborating with experts in product, design, and operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Familiarity with functional programming languages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Experience driving initiatives at a broader level across an organization or company&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Strong writing skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Proactive approach&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Must be working in Canada at the start of role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please be aware, job-seekers may be at risk of targeting by malicious actors looking for personal data. Brex recruiters will only reach out via LinkedIn or email with a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="http://brex.com/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="http://brex.com" data-sk="tooltip_parent"&gt;brex.com&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;domain. Any outreach claiming to be from Brex via other sources should be ignored.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;See yourself at Twilio&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join the team as our next Technical Program Manager - Staff on Twilio’s TDA-Flex product team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &amp;amp; why we’re hiring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Twilio powers real-time business communications and data solutions that help &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://customers.twilio.com/"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;companies and developers worldwide&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; build better applications and customer experiences.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although we're headquartered in San Francisco, we have presence throughout South America, Europe, Asia and Australia. We're on a journey to becoming a global company that actively opposes racism and all forms of oppression and bias. At Twilio, we support &lt;a href="https://www.twilio.com/company/diversity"&gt;diversity, equity &amp;amp; inclusion&lt;/a&gt; wherever we do business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Twilio is the world’s leading customer engagement platform empowering developers to build modern communication applications and experiences.&amp;nbsp; We seek an inspired and technical individual to join our Twilio Data &amp;amp; Applications Operations team. This team consists of Technical Delivery Program Management, Product Analytics and GTM program partnership. Individuals in this organization are dedicated to ensure successful product delivery from ideation to launch. As a Staff Technical Program Manager, you will be responsible for leading complex programs and evolving systems to create a more integrated and effective product delivery process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for enabling Program teams to reach their goals. You will ensure team collaboration and identify dependencies and risks, resolve blockers, track and report progress, all while leveraging best practices to ensure predictable and timely delivery of our programs. You will be partnering and collaborating with a variety of stakeholders from Product, Engineering, Sales, Professional services and support to craft a thoughtful ecosystem for partnership and ensuring that Twilio meets the needs of the market and customer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are excited about building and leading complex programs while creating clarity within ambiguous environments with a highly dedicated team to build something great, you will be a fantastic fit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;In this role, you’ll:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and lead complex cross-functional programs for product and cross-company initiatives. Must be able to effectively plan, organize and drive projects to completion with minimal oversight.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive towards continuous improvement through analyzing data and inspecting &amp;amp; adapting practices to work with agile teams to improve project delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the transparency and communication of the health and progress of an overall program that you are coordinating. Ability to effectively communicate across all levels of the organization including leading complex discussions with senior leaders by answering tough questions and effectively raising issues or areas of misalignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and analyze large amounts of information quickly in order to problem solve and drive decision-making effectively including technical design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain alignment within a highly dynamic and ambiguous situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and escalate gaps and risks across organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dependency management- Ability to identify, negotiate and monitor dependencies across multiple teams within the program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align senior leaders on program priorities. Regularly communicate program risks and align leaders on solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a sense of urgency and ownership to drive solutions and tasks to completion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help be an agent of change as we strengthen our Program Management across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simplify complexity to map out a program’s next steps and communicate an easily digestible plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the definition, development and tracking of effective metrics and R&amp;amp;D improvements that drive improved BU operating performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Not all applicants will have skills that match a job description exactly. Twilio values diverse experiences in other industries, and we encourage everyone who meets the required qualifications to apply. While having “desired” qualifications make for a strong candidate, we encourage applicants with alternative experiences to also apply. If your career is just starting or hasn't followed a traditional path, don't let that stop you from considering Twilio. We are always looking for people who will bring something new to the table!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+&amp;nbsp; years experience in technical program management, project management, or operational role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS degree in computer science or similar degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading and managing the successful delivery of high impact and highly cross-functional integrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to quickly build relationships and establish rapport with various cross-functional stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to create clarity and movement in ambiguous situations with a passion to deliver innovative solutions at scale&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills as well as ability to think clearly, problem-solve and prioritize&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to adapt to and manage change.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to handle multiple competing priorities in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification in Project Management or relevant discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in delivering complex programs in an Agile environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in establishing and driving the adoption of program frameworks, tools, and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with SaaS products. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Atlassian suite tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;This role will be remote in the US, preferably in the&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; East Coast.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;There are many benefits to working at Twilio, including, in addition to competitive pay, things like generous time-off, ample parental and wellness leave, healthcare, a retirement savings program, and much more. Offerings vary by location.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Twilio thinks big. Do you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;We like to solve problems, take initiative, pitch in when needed, and are always up for trying new things. That's why we seek out colleagues who embody our values — something we call&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.twilio.com/company/values"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; Twilio Magic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;. Additionally, we empower employees to build&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.twilio.org/impact-fund/"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; positive change in their communities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; by supporting their volunteering and donation efforts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;So, if you're ready to unleash your full potential, do your best work, and be the best version of yourself, apply now!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;If this role isn't what you're looking for, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.twilio.com/company/jobs#open-positions"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;please consider other open positions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The estimated pay ranges for this role are as follows:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Based in Colorado:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; $ 132,320&amp;nbsp; - $ 165,400 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Based in New York, Washington State or California (outside the San Francisco Bay Area):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; $ 140,080 - $175,100 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;This role is NOT eligible to hire in the bay area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;This role may be eligible to participate in Twilio’s equity plan. All roles are eligible for the following benefits: health care insurance, 401(k) retirement account, paid sick time, paid personal time off, paid parental leave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;The successful candidate’s starting salary will be determined based on permissible, non-discriminatory factors such as skills, experience, and geographic location within the state.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Twilio is proud to be an equal opportunity employer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Twilio is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity&amp;nbsp;and Affirmative Action&amp;nbsp;employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, reproductive health decisions, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, genetic information, political views or activity, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. Additionally, Twilio participates in the E-Verify program in certain locations, as required by law.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Twilio is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability,&amp;nbsp;please&amp;nbsp;contact us at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="mailto:accommodation@twilio.com" target="_blank"&gt;accommodation@twilio.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe’s mission is to grow the GDP of the internet. Often, this is through abstracting complex and frustrating tasks to make them simple, so that Stripe users can focus on growing their businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the most common requests from our users is to help them with indirect tax compliance as they expand their business.&amp;nbsp; We handle billions of dollars each year and enable millions of users around the world to scale faster and more efficiently by building their businesses on Stripe. The GIS (Geographical Information Systems) Tax Analyst will be a key team member as we build and maintain leading indirect tax features, tools, services, and other automation solutions for our users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our indirect tax technology and product team is comprised of tax professionals and software engineers that are responsible for building and maintaining end-to-end global transaction tax solutions (sales and use tax, VAT, GST, and other indirect taxes) for thousands of merchants that use Stripe software and API’s for payments and managing their business online. At Stripe, we are committed to building simple, user-friendly products and for this reason we are seeking a world-class Tax GIS Analyst to join the team!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain the GIS which informs and facilitates the operation and maintenance of Stripe's tax products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct data gathering, conversion, and analysis of GIS data and prepare data documentation and metadata for the Stripe Tax GIS jurisdiction determination services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor jurisdiction boundary and other data changes and update content accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain repeatable and scalable automation tests to monitor GIS data and conformance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain automated processes useful to the jurisdiction content update and deployment process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve user contacts and incidents relevant to GIS and&amp;nbsp; jurisdiction content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform in-depth analyses, develop recommendations, and advise on an as-needed basis to address complex GIS problems/issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate across product and eng teams to ensure successful delivery of data, products, and services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;We're looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of relevant working experience in GIS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree from an accredited university in GIS, Geography, Computer Science or a related field or equivalent combination of education and experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using ArcGIS for managing jurisdiction boundaries including creating, analyzing, and compiling boundary data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with tabular data development and maintenance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced proficiency with Python, SQL, Excel, VBA, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience and/or knowledge with GIS work in supporting indirect tax automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data engineering and database design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with software development in Java..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with leading tax automation solutions (Vertex, Avalara, Sovos, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;At Cloudflare, we have our eyes set on an ambitious goal: to help build a better Internet. Today the company runs one of the world’s largest networks that powers approximately 25 million Internet properties, for customers ranging from individual bloggers to SMBs to Fortune 500 companies. Cloudflare protects and accelerates any Internet application online without adding hardware, installing software, or changing a line of code. Internet properties powered by Cloudflare all have web traffic routed through its intelligent global network, which gets smarter with every request. As a result, they see significant improvement in performance and a decrease in spam and other attacks. Cloudflare was named to Entrepreneur Magazine’s Top Company Cultures list and ranked among the World’s Most Innovative Companies by Fast Company.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;We realize people do not fit into neat boxes. We are looking for curious and empathetic individuals who are committed to developing themselves and learning new skills, and we are ready to help you do that. We cannot complete our mission without building a diverse and inclusive team. We hire the best people based on an evaluation of their potential and support them throughout their time at Cloudflare. Come join us!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cloudflare’s Engineering Team builds and runs the software that handles a large number of HTTP requests on the Internet today. We also build and run the internal tools that builds and runs our software. The Engineering Team is split into two groups: one handles product development and the other handles operations. Product development covers both new features and functionality and scaling our existing software to meet the challenges of a massively growing customer base. The operations team handles one of the world’s largest networks with data centers in 102 cities worldwide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you'll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cloudflare is looking for a Senior Backend engineer to help us build and maintain the codebase that powers both our customer APIs as well as internal service APIs. This is a role for engineers that are familiar with standard backend backend architecture, and capable in database design and interaction. Our API platform is under constant load and scrutiny, so experience and commitment to easily understood and test code is also a key part of the role. Your ability to visualize the flow of data through a complex application is critical to your success, and to the team’s. You will be working closely with the product team to understand and document the functional needs of their product requirements, developing new code to solve new problems, as well as maintaining existing code to squash bugs. Our tech stack includes services built using Go, PHP, Redis, Postgres, and Cloudflare products (e.g. Workers). We are looking for proficiency in RESTful API design, relational databases (SQL), and modern containerized deployment practices. Knowledge of PHP is not a must, but deep familiarity with web favored languages is (Go).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of desirable skills, knowledge and experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 6 years of professional experience building and managing software applications at large scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge of at least one modern programming language such as Go, Rust, JavaScript, PHP with strong computer science fundamentals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in designing and architecting large-scale distributed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for Observability (experience with Prometheus, Grafana, and Kibana are a plus, but not required).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing, implementing, and documenting customer-facing APIs are a huge plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid knowledge of SQL and common relational database systems such as PostgreSQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience debugging, optimizing and identifying possible failures in a large-scale distributed system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Kubernetes, Kafka.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to negotiate and work with product managers to gather requirements is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience being in a Technical lead or Team lead role is a huge plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation may be adjusted depending on work location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For Colorado-based hires: Estimated annual salary of $&lt;span data-sheets-value="{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:3,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:168000}" data-sheets-userformat="{&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:14845,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;#,##0&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:1},&amp;quot;5&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:[{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;5&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0}},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:3},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;4&amp;quot;:1}]},&amp;quot;6&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:[{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;5&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0}},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:3},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;4&amp;quot;:1}]},&amp;quot;7&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:[{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;5&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0}},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:3},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;4&amp;quot;:1}]},&amp;quot;8&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:[{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;5&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0}},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:3},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;4&amp;quot;:1}]},&amp;quot;9&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;10&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;11&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;14&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:3,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:1},&amp;quot;15&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Open Sans&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;16&amp;quot;:11}" data-sheets-formula="=if(if(R[-10]C[0]=&amp;quot;Hire&amp;quot;,iferror(round(R[0]C[1]*0.9,-3),&amp;quot;&amp;quot;),iferror(round(R[0]C[1]*0.8,-3),&amp;quot;&amp;quot;))=0,&amp;q