&lt;p&gt;Personal development and&amp;nbsp;becoming&amp;nbsp;the best&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;you&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;is all about growth and exploring new skills and opportunities – both in and out of the office. At Accruent, we call this Grow Without Limits, and we’re proud to offer each of our employees the resources, coaching and support necessary to achieve Growth Without Limits in their personal and professional lives. Explore where the path takes you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Sales Incentive Administrator plays a crucial role in supporting a company's sales team by managing and administering various sales incentive programs. Their primary responsibility is to participate in design of incentive plans and SPIFs, and to implement, and maintain incentive programs that motivate sales representatives and drive revenue growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Sales Incentive Administrator&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary: &lt;/strong&gt;The Sales Incentive Administrator is responsible for managing, and administering sales incentive programs to motivate and reward the sales team for achieving targets and objectives! They will work closely with the Sales, Finance and Payroll teams to ensure that incentive programs are effective in driving sales performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt; Collect and analyze sales performance data to determine program effectiveness and make data-driven decisions for program improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Clearly communicate program details, rules, and expectations to the sales team, ensuring they understand the incentive structure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation:&lt;/strong&gt; Maintain comprehensive records of incentive program rules, terms, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure that sales representatives meet the eligibility criteria to participate in incentive programs and address any eligibility concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculations:&lt;/strong&gt; Accurately calculate and validate incentive payments based on predefined criteria, such as quotas, commissions, bonuses, and other performance metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting:&lt;/strong&gt; Generate regular reports and summaries of incentive program results, performance, and payouts for management and team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure that incentive programs follow legal and regulatory requirements, as well as company policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feedback and Improvement:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate with the sales team to gather feedback on incentive programs and make necessary adjustments for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conflict Resolution:&lt;/strong&gt; Address and resolve disputes and inquiries related to incentive calculations or program rules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technology Utilization:&lt;/strong&gt; Use software and tools, including CRM and incentive management software, to automate and streamline the administration of incentive programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training and Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide training and support to sales representatives to help them understand the incentive program and maximize their earnings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience in business, finance, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in sales incentive administration or a similar role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and data management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in using CRM, Excel and incentive management software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and accuracy in incentive calculations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of sales processes and incentive standard methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of legal and compliance regulations related to sales incentives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Problem-solving and conflict resolution skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and time management abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This job may require travel domestically and/or internationally,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a full-time, exempt opportunity.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation will not be considered for this position.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At this time, visa sponsorship is not available.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Base pay offered may vary depending on various factors, including, but not limited to: job-related knowledge; skills; experience; and other eligibility factors such as geographic location. The Total Rewards package includes competitive base pay and an opportunity to enroll in a variety of benefit programs, generally including health insurance, flexible spending accounts, health savings accounts, retirement savings plans, life and disability insurance programs, and several programs that provide for both paid and unpaid time away from work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT ACCRUENT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Accruent (a subsidiary or affiliate of Fortive Corporation), we strive to be on the cutting edge of the software world, providing purpose-built intelligent solutions that raise customer expectations, shift paradigms and transform the way businesses operate and achieve success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We aim to provide the same transformational growth for our 1,000+ employees which includes a vibrant office culture in major cities like Austin and Amsterdam – and 10,000 customers in more than 150 countries – we know you’ll gain new experiences along the way. In our continued effort to help our teams Grow Without Limits, we provide all employees with the resources, coaching and support they need to reach new heights and experience true professional and personal development – and we do this because we believe it will help us grow as a global company in return.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every person can bring something incredible to the table, and we can always achieve more together. So, if you are courageous, adaptable, collaborative and interested in becoming the best you, we encourage you to join us for the ride – even if you don’t believe you have the exact experience to fill a particular role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Explore the path. Join Accruent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT FORTIVE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortive’s essential technology makes the world stronger, safer, and smarter. We accelerate transformation across a broad range of applications including environmental, health and safety compliance, industrial condition monitoring, next-generation product design, and healthcare safety solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a global industrial technology innovator with a startup spirit. Our forward-looking companies lead the way in software-powered workflow solutions, data-driven intelligence, AI-powered automation, and other disruptive technologies. We’re a force for progress, working alongside our customers and partners to solve challenges on a global scale, from workplace safety in the most demanding conditions to groundbreaking sustainability solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a diverse team 17,000 strong, united by a dynamic, inclusive culture and energized by limitless learning and growth. We use the proven Fortive Business System (FBS) to accelerate our positive impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Fortive, we believe in you. We believe in your potential—your ability to learn, grow, and make a difference. At Fortive, we believe in us. We believe in the power of people working together to solve problems no one could solve alone. At Fortive, we believe in growth. We’re honest about what’s working and what isn’t, and we never stop improving and innovating.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortive: For you, for us, for growth.&lt;/p&gt;
