&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHO WE ARE:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ActBlue is a nonprofit that builds tech and infrastructure for Democratic campaigns, progressive-aligned causes, and people trying to make an impact in order to fuel long-term, people-powered change. If you’ve ever given online to a Democrat or progressive organization, chances are you’ve used our powerful online fundraising platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We put power in the hands of small-dollar donors and help thousands of groups — from presidential candidates to environmental organizations — build grassroots movements. We envision a democracy where everyone looking to make progressive people-powered change can easily and effectively deploy their resources, energy, and creativity to shape our country and futures. Each and every one of us, from the political activists to the tech innovators to the customer service pros, is fully committed to our mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE OPPORTUNITY:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Communications and Marketing Team is responsible for managing ActBlue’s communications, as well as our online and in-person presence. The Press Associate will help monitor direct press hits and wider industry coverage; promote the incredible work small-dollar donors around the country are doing, both internally and externally; and work with the rest of the team to achieve strategic teamwide goals. This position is perfect for someone passionate about politics, advocacy, and our mission of empowering small-dollar donors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The person in this role is expected to work Eastern Standard Time hours, due to the nature of the role in driving the day’s press work across the organization and the importance of keeping up with news from Washington, D.C..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU WILL DO:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor direct and indirect press hits daily, including sending morning news clips to the entire organization (expected by 8:30 AM ET).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor press and media trends through media monitoring/social listening platforms and distribute real time updates to relevant stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with our outside PR firm to respond to press requests, ensuring requests are handled by reporter deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help write op-eds, press releases, and internal and external talking points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Watch live and monitor congressional hearings, Supreme Court decisions, campaign launches, debates, protests, and other political or advocacy events as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help coordinate the release of sitewide fundraising numbers and other ActBlue-driven narratives via blog post, press release, social media, and other channels to maximize press coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Copy edit and fact check communications with the press.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in rapid response moments, keep an eye on incoming media requests outside of working hours, including weekends, and occasionally work early mornings, nights, and weekends as needed (sometimes on short notice based on what’s happening politically or stories that we are expecting to drop).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the first to know about new developments in online fundraising, Democratic politics, nonprofit fundraising, and campaign finance law.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the ActBlue blog as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU BRING:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on a campaign, with a related political organization, a PR/communications agency, or news outlet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing for multiple audiences, such as members of the press, clients, and the general public.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills including an ability to communicate across multiple mediums with multiple stakeholders and strong writing and copy editing skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong judgment and discretion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and translate complex data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in growing external networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to prioritize multiple competing projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incredible dedication to detail — you should sweat the small stuff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment that can change at a moment’s notice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated commitment to diversity and inclusion in all dimensions of your work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in campaign finance laws and legislation and a passion for politics, organizing, and small-dollar fundraising.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
