&lt;p&gt;Upwork ($UPWK) is the world’s work marketplace. We serve everyone from one-person startups to large, Fortune 100 enterprises with a powerful, trust-driven platform that enables companies and talent to work together in new ways that unlock their potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last year, more than $3.8 billion of work was done through Upwork by skilled professionals who are gaining more control by finding work they are passionate about and innovating their careers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p class="rich-text-toolbar"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;The Sr Director of Next Gen Search at Upwork will bring to life the future of search capabilities at Upwork, enhancing how we connect talent with opportunities and clients. By leveraging syntactic, semantic, contextual, and structural search dimensions, and incorporating voice, text, and video integrations, this role is critical to enabling transformational product experiences..&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Collaborating closely with our multi-disciplinary teams, the ideal candidate will possess a robust technical understanding of search algorithms, rankings, and relevance, guiding us towards our mission of creating the most efficient and rewarding work marketplace.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Your Responsibilities:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Drive the evolution of search experiences in our marketplace, ensuring optimized user experience for both talents and hiring managers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Remain at the forefront of search technology by integrating the latest advancements, including:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Neural-based retrieval methods for deeper contextual understanding.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Multimodal search capabilities, encompassing voice, text, and video search.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Semantic search techniques for improved relevance and comprehension.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;AI-driven predictive search for proactive recommendation systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Real-time indexing for faster, up-to-date search results.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Enhanced natural language processing (NLP) for better query understanding and response.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Responsible for both the strategy and execution of this function, overseeing PMs, ontologists, and the expansive ontology utilized across Upwork’s platform.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams, including designers, engineers, machine learning and AI scientists, analysts, ontologists, and product marketers, ensuring the successful rollout of cross-product initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Establish, monitor, and refine key search metrics, continuously utilizing quantitative tests to gain insights and improve search efficiency across the Upwork ecosystem.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Remain updated on the latest advancements in search technologies, ensuring Upwork remains at the forefront of next-gen search capabilities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and nurture a team of product managers, enhancing their skills in product management and emphasizing the creation of high-performing search experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;What it takes to catch our eye:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Proven experience in leading innovative search teams and delivering state-of-the-art search and recommendation experiences.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Demonstrated knowledge in developing and/or leading taxonomy, ontology, or standardization initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Strong command over the technicalities of search, including ontology, taxonomy, and data models, to engage effectively in discussions with tech-savvy team members.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Exceptional communication skills, with the ability to articulate complex topics clearly, align various stakeholders, and maintain a strong executive presence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;A proven track record of understanding customer requirements and ensuring effective collaboration across multifaceted teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;An unwavering passion for Upwork’s mission and a genuine appreciation for our platform's transformative potential.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class="rich-text-toolbar"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400; color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The annual base salary for this position in California and Washington ranges from $218,000 - $310,000. The range displayed reflects the minimum and maximum salary for this position in California and Washington, and individual base pay will depend on your skills, qualifications, experience, and location. Additionally, this position is eligible for the annual bonus plan or sales incentive plan and eligibility to participate in our long term equity incentive program.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Come change how the world works.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;At Upwork, you’ll shape talent solutions for how the world works today. We are a remote-first organization working together to create exciting remote work opportunities for a global community of professionals.&amp;nbsp; While we have physical offices in San Francisco and Chicago, currently we also support hiring of corporate full-time employees in 19 states in the United States. Please speak with a member of our recruitment team to determine whether you are located in a state in which we are hiring corporate full-time employees.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Our vibrant culture is built on shared values and our mission to create economic opportunities so that people have better lives. We foster amazing teams, put our community first, and have a bias toward action. We encourage everyone to bring their whole selves to work and grow together through development opportunities, mentorship, and employee resource groups. And oh yeah, we've also got amazing benefits - including medical insurance for you and your family, unlimited PTO, 401(k) with matching, 12 weeks of paid parental leave, and a generous Employee Stock Purchase Plan. Check out our Life at Upwork page to learn more about our benefits and the employee experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Check out our &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://careers.upwork.com/life-at-upwork"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Life at Upwork&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt; page to learn more about the employee experience.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Upwork is proudly committed to recruiting and retaining a diverse and inclusive workforce. As an Equal Opportunity Employer, we never discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical condition), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, or other applicable legally protected characteristics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;#LI-Remote&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;To learn more about how Upwork processes and protects your personal information as part of the application process, please review our &lt;a href="http://upwork.com/careers/job-applicant-privacy-notice" target="_blank"&gt;Global Job Applicant Privacy Notice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a role that motivates and challenges you? Are you ready for an opportunity for growth? Do you want to work on teams where people roll up their sleeves to take on tough problems together, and regularly blow the doors off our clients with their outstanding teamwork? If you answered yes to those questions, 3Cloud might just be for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At 3Cloud, we hire people who aren’t afraid to experiment or fail. We hire people who are willing to give direct and candid feedback to their managers, leaders, and team members. We hire people who jump at those opportunities because they care about our collective growth and success. We hire people who challenge and hold each other accountable for living 3Cloud’s core values because they know that it will result in amazing experiences and solutions for our clients and each other.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview:&lt;/strong&gt; As a Solutions Architect for App Innovation at 3Cloud, you will be at the forefront of our mission to deliver cutting-edge solutions on the Azure platform. Your technical expertise, coupled with a strong understanding of our clients’ business needs, will be instrumental in driving innovative solutions and ensuring client satisfaction. You will closely collaborate with the sales teams to explore, design, and deliver solutions, thereby significantly contributing to our growth in the Azure ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client Engagement:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and nurture strong relationships with key client stakeholders, serving as a trusted advisor throughout their Azure-based technology transformation and App Innovation journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with customers, both onsite and remotely, by providing technical expertise during the sales process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sales Support:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide expertise to the sales team, supporting them in pursuing and closing engagements related to App Innovation and Azure-based solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with sales executives on strategy, pursuit, and closure of key opportunities, aiming to expand revenue influence and client satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solution Development:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with sales teams to ensure effective sales strategies and alignment with client needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the creation of reference architectures, documentation, and intellectual property that ensures secure, scalable, and profitable service delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development &amp;amp; Thought Leadership:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and deliver high-value and reusable enablement content that measurably improves the team’s effectiveness and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve your professional skills with a focus on personal mastery and team learning through activities such as training, reading, and seeking mentorship from others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration and Teamwork:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-departmentally to find solutions to complex scenarios and integration issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in team mentorship and knowledge sharing, fostering a culture of growth and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Service Line / Service Delivery Framework Development:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the ideation and development of internal and external solutions that support business initiatives and cross-practice opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the creation of accelerators, intellectual property, and innovative solutions that enhance services offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in cloud platforms, particularly Microsoft Azure, and familiarity with AWS and GCP is advantageous.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in pre-sales and sales support within a professional services organization, with a track record of successfully pursuing and closing engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical presentation and communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to provide constructive feedback and guidance to team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for enhancing client experiences and achieving business goals using cloud solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial mindset with a proactive approach to identifying and capitalizing on opportunities for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented with a commitment to delivering excellence and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Azure certification, such as Microsoft Certified: Azure Solutions Architect Expert, is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel if needed and comply with the company’s travel policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in App Innovation and solution development, with exposure to a wide range of cloud/Azure solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with modern software development and their associated technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in designing and developing cloud applications to meet client needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the end-to-end software development lifecycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud computing and related technologies and practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of continuous integration and continuous deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At 3Cloud, we value Client Success, Growth, and Winning Together. If you're ready to be part of a dedicated team pushing the boundaries of what's possible with Azure, we'd love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-pay-transparency"&gt;&lt;div class="pay-input"&gt;&lt;div class="description"&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3Cloud Total Rewards Highlights Include:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible work location with a virtual first approach to work! &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(K) with match up to 50% of your 6% contributions of eligible pay &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous PTO providing a minimum of 15 days in addition to 9 paid company holidays and 2 floating personal days &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Three medical plan options to allow you the choice to elect what works best for you! &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Option for vision and dental coverage &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;100% employer premium coverage for STD and LTD &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid leave for birth parents and non-birth parents &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Option for FSA, HSA, HRA and Dependent Care &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$67.00 monthly tech and home office allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilization and/or discretionary bonus eligibility based on role &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Robust Employee Assistance Program to help with everyday challenges &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
3Cloud offers competitive compensation. In addition to base pay employees are eligible to receive an annual discretionary/utilization bonus. If you are hired at 3Cloud your final base salary is based on factors such as skills, education, experience and/or geographic location. Please keep in mind that the range mentioned above includes the full base salary range for the role. It is not typical for offers to be made at or near the top of the range.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="title"&gt;Base Salary Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="pay-range"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$169,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="divider"&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$203,000 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Don’t meet every single requirement?&amp;nbsp;At 3Cloud we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At this time, we cannot sponsor applicants for work visas.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reddit is a community of communities where people can dive into anything through experiences built around their interests, hobbies, and passions. Our mission is to bring community, belonging, and empowerment to everyone in the world. Reddit users submit, vote, and comment on content, stories, and discussions about the topics they care about the most. From pets to parenting, there’s a community for everybody on Reddit and with over 50 million daily active users, it is home to the most open and authentic conversations on the internet. For more information, visit &lt;a href="redditinc.com" target="_blank"&gt;redditinc.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reddit has an amazing history of individual and community-driven innovation. With no official support, thousands of user scripts, self-identified bots and services run against our API and enrich the experience Redditors have on our platform. Furthermore, the value of Reddit data has powered the creation and growth of numerous businesses. The goal of the Reddit Developer Platform team is to further empower communities to innovate while establishing a significant new business centered on our Data API.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Staff Product Manager with a strong technical background to lead our Data API. You will play a pivotal role in not only evolving the existing Data API, but also spearheading initiatives to monetize API products effectively.&amp;nbsp;This is a unique opportunity to join a key pillar of one of the most important consumer products on the Internet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a product strategy for our API product suite, setting vision, goals and roadmaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams including Engineering, UX/UI Design, Marketing, and Customer Support to deliver high-quality API products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market research to identify user needs, trends, and competitive opportunities to enhance API offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop comprehensive product requirements and documentation to drive API development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize and manage development backlogs, ensuring timelines and deliverables are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure and analyze API performance, usage, and adoption, and drive continuous improvement based on findings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a product evangelist, fostering relationships with the developer community and promoting API products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the creation of developer resources, such as documentation, tutorials, and sample code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and exploit revenue generation opportunities through innovative API product development and enhancement initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 5+ years of experience as a Product Manager, ideally for developer-facing products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coding experience, with proficiency in at least one programming language (e.g. Python, TypeScript, JavaScript).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of API design, development, and lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and decision-making skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to convey complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear passion for Reddit and it’s mission&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in managing and delivering API products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Reddit’s APIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MBA or advanced degree in a relevant field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive Health benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401k Matching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Workspace benefits for your home office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal &amp;amp; Professional development funds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Family Planning Support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Vacation (please use them!) &amp;amp; Reddit Global Days Off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ months paid Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Volunteer time off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-value="{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;#LI-AS5&amp;quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:33554945,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:0},&amp;quot;12&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;28&amp;quot;:1}"&gt;#LI-AS5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-pay-transparency"&gt;&lt;div class="pay-input"&gt;&lt;div class="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Transparency:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This job posting may span more than one career level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to base salary, this job is eligible to receive equity in the form of restricted stock units, and depending on the position offered, it may also be eligible to receive a commission. Additionally, Reddit offers a wide range of benefits to U.S.-based employees, including medical, dental, and vision insurance, 401(k) program with employer match, generous time off for vacation, and parental leave. To learn more, please visit &lt;a href="https://www.redditinc.com/careers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;https://www.redditinc.com/careers/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide greater transparency to candidates, we share base pay ranges for all US-based job postings regardless of state. We set standard base pay ranges for all roles based on function, level, and country location, benchmarked against similar stage growth companies. Final offer amounts are determined by multiple factors including, skills, depth of work experience and relevant licenses/credentials, and may vary from the amounts listed below.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="title"&gt;The base pay range for this position is:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="pay-range"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$198,200&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="divider"&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$297,300 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Reddit is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability, please contact us at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:ApplicationAssistance@Reddit.com"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;ApplicationAssistance@Reddit.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The GitLab&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://about.gitlab.com/solutions/devops-platform/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://about.gitlab.com/solutions/devops-platform/" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;DevSecOps platform&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;empowers 100,000+ organizations to deliver software faster and more efficiently. We are one of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/all-remote/guide/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/all-remote/guide/" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;world’s largest all-remote companies&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;with 2,000+ team members and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://handbook.gitlab.com/handbook/values/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/values/" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;values&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;that foster a culture where people embrace the belief that everyone can contribute. Learn more about&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://vimeo.com/778157354" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://vimeo.com/778157354" data-sk="tooltip_parent" data-remove-tab-index="true"&gt;Life at GitLab&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Remote, Western Europe&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An overview of this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an individual contributor reporting to the Sr Director of Global Field Enablement, you will build and deploy product enablement programs and training curricula to help our customer-facing field teams build a deeper technical understanding of our product use cases, effectively demonstrate and clearly differentiate our platform capabilities, and successfully articulate the power of GitLab’s AI-Powered DevSecOps platform.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will partner with Technical Marketing, Product Marketing and Management, Solutions Architecture &amp;amp; Field CTO, Customer Success, Customer Education, and various other field team members to build quantitatively measurable product enablement for our customer-facing teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a builder, if you enjoy working with technical go-to-market teams, and if experiential lab-based training and scenario-based enablement sounds exciting, then you should apply.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and define technical sales capability models and product knowledge skills matrices for multiple roles (Account Executives, Customer Success Managers, Solution Architects, and Professional Services)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, deploy, maintain, and report on blended learning solutions and pathways by role (digital self-service, experiential/labs, instructor-led workshops, assessments, and technical accreditations).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run bi-annual (2x per year) self and manager skills assessments mapped to the skills matrices and report on the continuous progress improvements and opportunities or skill gaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage a repository of consumable product training, demo videos, labs and workshops, and other resources for digital self-service consumption.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate regularly with Customer Success, Solutions Architecture, Technical Marketing, and Customer Education teams to align on product enablement plans and learning paths.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and report on the success of all product enablement programs and training, including business outcomes like use case adoption, effective proof of value and trial execution, pipeline generation, product competitive differentiation and customer messaging (at scale), and efficient pipeline stage progression.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build manager coaching resources and accreditations for scaled on-the-job reinforcement and sustainment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain in-depth knowledge of the entire GitLab application and use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years experience building product enablement programs and curricula for B2B enterprise sales and/or experience in a technical software sales or a technical sales enablement role, solutions engineering or architecture teams, preferably with expertise in DevOps and/or Open Source software&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Introductory knowledge and subject matter familiarity with modern software development and their associated technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the end-to-end software development lifecycle, security and governance, and continuous integration and continuous deployment, is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to use GitLab and willing to work with Git and GitLab whenever possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing technical documentation and building experiential learning programs using virtual lab environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical, analytical, and problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-manages workload to meet deadlines and prioritize accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills and ability to gather feedback and build consensus with multiple stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detailed oriented and analytical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The GitLab Field Enablement team exists to inspire our field and partners to achieve high levels of success through the acquisition and application of knowledge, skills and behaviors - at scale - that improve productivity and accelerate customer outcomes &amp;amp; growth. We have a lot of fun doing this!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thanks to our &lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/values/#transparency"&gt;Transparency&lt;/a&gt; value, you can learn more about our Field Enablement strategy and programs on our &lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/sales/field-operations/field-enablement/"&gt;Field Enablement Team Handbook&lt;/a&gt; page.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How GitLab will support you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/"&gt;Benefits to support your health, finances, and well-being&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/all-remote/guide/"&gt;All remote&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/all-remote/asynchronous/"&gt;asynchronous&lt;/a&gt; work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/paid-time-off/"&gt;Flexible Paid Time Off&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/inclusion/erg-guide/#:~:text=Definition%20of%20the%20TMRG%20%2D%20Team%20Member%20Resource%20Groups,-TMRGs%20are%20voluntary&amp;amp;text=The%20purpose%20for%20this%20type,developing%20the%20sense%20of%20belonging."&gt;Team Member Resource Groups&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/stock-options/"&gt;Equity Compensation &amp;amp; Employee Stock Purchase Plan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/#growth-and-development-benefit"&gt;Growth and development budget&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/total-rewards/benefits/general-and-entity-benefits/#parental-leave"&gt;Parental leave&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/finance/procurement/office-equipment-supplies/"&gt;Home office&lt;/a&gt; support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that we welcome interest from candidates with varying levels of experience; many successful candidates do not meet every single requirement. Additionally, studies have shown that people from &lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/company/culture/inclusion/#examples-of-select-underrepresented-groups"&gt;underrepresented groups&lt;/a&gt; are less likely to apply to a job unless they meet every single qualification. If you're excited about this role, please apply and allow our recruiters to assess your application.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Country Hiring Guidelines: &lt;/strong&gt;GitLab hires new team members in countries around the world. All of our roles are remote, however some roles may carry specific location-based eligibility requirements. Our Talent Acquisition team can help answer any questions about location after starting the recruiting process.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Privacy Policy: &lt;/strong&gt;Please review our &lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/hiring/candidate/faq/recruitment-privacy-policy/" target="_blank"&gt;Recruitment Privacy Policy.&lt;/a&gt; Your privacy is important to us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GitLab is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. GitLab’s policies and practices relating to recruitment, employment, career development and advancement, promotion, and retirement are based solely on merit, regardless of race, color, religion, ancestry, sex (including pregnancy, lactation, sexual orientation, gender identity, or gender expression), national origin, age, citizenship, marital status, mental or physical disability, genetic information (including family medical history), discharge status from the military, protected veteran status (which includes disabled veterans, recently separated veterans, active duty wartime or campaign badge veterans, and Armed Forces service medal veterans), or any other basis protected by law. GitLab will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics. See also&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/people-policies/inc-usa/#equal-employment-opportunity-policy" target="_blank"&gt;GitLab’s EEO Policy&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/labor-and-employment-notices/#eeoc-us-equal-employment-opportunity-commission-notices" target="_blank"&gt;EEO is the Law&lt;/a&gt;. If you have a disability or special need that requires&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/people-policies/inc-usa/#reasonable-accommodation" target="_blank"&gt;accommodation&lt;/a&gt;, please let us know during the&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://about.gitlab.com/handbook/hiring/interviewing/#adjustments-to-our-interview-process" target="_blank"&gt;recruiting process&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;See yourself at Twilio&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join the team as Twilio’s next Manager, GTM Field Enablement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are &amp;amp; why we’re hiring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Twilio powers real-time business communications and data solutions that help &lt;a href="https://customers.twilio.com/"&gt;companies and developers worldwide&lt;/a&gt; build better applications and customer experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although we're headquartered in San Francisco, we have presence throughout South America, Europe, Asia and Australia. We're on a journey to becoming a global company that actively opposes racism and all forms of oppression and bias. At Twilio, we support &lt;a href="https://www.twilio.com/company/diversity"&gt;diversity, equity &amp;amp; inclusion&lt;/a&gt; wherever we do business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person in this position will report directly to the Head of GTM Enablement working closely with their peers in the GTM Enablement organization as we continue to transform the business and state of Enablement. If you like adding value and seeing the direct impact of your work while thriving in highly dynamic environments and love rolling your sleeves up to get things done, this role is for you. This is a people leader role.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Head of GTM Enablement to develop quarterly enablement plans and lead the Field Enablement Business Partners to execute the plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute on a plan to establish and conduct Leadership Development programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customize and deliver content tailored by audience leveraging cutting edge enablement tools&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help coach sellers to ensure skills are mastered&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working independently and as part of a team, specifically coming with experience developing strong cross functional relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide thought leadership to the organization through contributions to knowledge bases, training sessions, knowledge development, weekly updates&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain knowledge of Twilio’s competitor’s products, company direction, financial stability, etc&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop team of GTM Field Enablement Business Partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not all applicants will have skills that match a job description exactly. Twilio values diverse experiences in other industries, and we encourage everyone who meets the required qualifications to apply. While having “desired” qualifications make for a strong candidate, we encourage applicants with alternative experiences to also apply. If your career is just starting or hasn't followed a traditional path, don't let that stop you from considering Twilio. We are always looking for people who will bring something new to the table!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in Enterprise B2B Enablement or training in a high-tech environment. Prior sales experience is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience leveraging enablement best practices, sales processes, sales coaching and sales methodologies.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training delivery and facilitation skills with experience delivering virtual instructor led sessions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of LMS systems, enablement tools such as Gong, Highspot or other content management systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capable of leveraging adult learning theory to develop enablement programs, content and assets that enable just-in-time, on-demand learnings with measurable outcomes tied to business objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience delivering leadership development programs having certifications in coaching, leadership development programs and/or sales methodologies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience delivering leadership development programs having certifications in coaching, leadership development programs and/or sales methodologies&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior leadership experience though we are open to a first time leader&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be remote&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;but is not eligible to be hired in San Francisco, CA, Oakland, CA, San Jose, CA, or the surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Notes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;*Please note this role is open to candidates outside of Colorado, California, New York, and Washington. The information below is provided for candidates hired in those locations only.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The estimated pay ranges for this role are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in Colorado: $120,160 - $150,200.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in New York, Washington State, or California (outside of the San Francisco Bay area): $127,280 - $159,100.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in the San Francisco Bay area, California: $141,360 - $176,700.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role may be eligible to participate in Twilio’s equity plan. All roles are eligible for the following benefits: health care insurance, 401(k) retirement account, paid sick time, paid personal time off, paid parental leave.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate’s starting salary will be determined based on permissible, non-discriminatory factors such as skills, experience, and geographic location within the state.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are many benefits to working at Twilio, including, in addition to competitive pay, things like generous time-off, ample parental and wellness leave, healthcare, a retirement savings program, and much more. Offerings vary by location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Twilio thinks big. Do you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We like to solve problems, take initiative, pitch in when needed, and are always up for trying new things. That's why we seek out colleagues who embody our values — something we call &lt;a href="https://www.twilio.com/company/values"&gt;Twilio Magic&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, we empower employees to build &lt;a href="https://twilio.org/support-and-resources/impact-fund"&gt;positive change in their communities&lt;/a&gt; by supporting their volunteering and donation efforts.&amp;nbsp; So, if you're ready to unleash your full potential, do your best work, and be the best version of yourself, apply now! If this role isn't what you're looking for, &lt;a href="https://www.twilio.com/company/jobs#open-positions"&gt;please consider other open positions&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Twilio is proud to be an equal opportunity employer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Twilio is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity&amp;nbsp;and Affirmative Action&amp;nbsp;employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, reproductive health decisions, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, genetic information, political views or activity, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. Additionally, Twilio participates in the E-Verify program in certain locations, as required by law.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Twilio is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities and disabled veterans in our job application procedures. If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability,&amp;nbsp;please&amp;nbsp;contact us at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="mailto:accommodation@twilio.com" target="_blank"&gt;accommodation@twilio.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;With electric vehicles expected to be nearly 30% of new vehicle sales by 2025 and more than 50% by 2040, electric mobility is becoming a reality. ChargePoint (NYSE: CHPT) is at the center of this revolution, powering one of the world’s leading EV charging networks and a comprehensive set of hardware, software and mobile solutions for every charging need across North America and Europe. We bring together drivers, businesses, automakers, policymakers, utilities and other stakeholders to make e-mobility a global reality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Since our founding in 2007, ChargePoint has focused solely on making the transition to electric easy for businesses, fleets and drivers. ChargePoint offers a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to create an all-electric future and a trillion-dollar market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;At ChargePoint, we foster a positive and productive work environment by committing to live our values of Be Courageous, Charge Together, Love our Customers, Operate with Openness, and Relentlessly Pursue Awesome. These values guide how we show up every day, align, and work together to build a brighter future for all of us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Join the team that is building the EV charging industry and make your mark on how people and goods will get everywhere they need to go, in any context, for generations to come.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Discover what it’s like to help build the fueling network of the future - check out our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://www.chargepoint.com/engineering/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://www.chargepoint.com/engineering/" data-sk="tooltip_parent"&gt;Engineering Blog.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Senior Channel Sales Operations Manager&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced data-driven Senior Channel Sales Operations Manager to join our dynamic team. The primary responsibility of this role is to leverage data and analytics to optimize our channel sales forecasting processes. You will be responsible for providing strategic insights, making data-backed recommendations, and streamlining processes related to the bookings and billings forecast. The Channel Sales Operations Manager should be proactive, data-savvy, and possess excellent interpersonal and collaboration skills to drive results in a dynamic sales environment, especially when working alongside various partners in the channel ecosystem. This critical role will play a key part in enhancing our channel sales forecasting efficiency and overall performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Reporting to&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sr. Director, Sales Operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze historical sales, distributor inventory, and sell-through data to discern patterns, identify opportunities, and address challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop data models and algorithms to support accurate billings forecasts and provide stocking order recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage large datasets from internal systems and external channel partners and perform regular data quality and data integrity audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to create accurate and actionable billings forecasts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee channel order shipments and returns, price adjustments and make data-informed recommendations to refine existing processes ensuring efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Streamline channel sales processes by identifying bottlenecks and proposing improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend adjustments to sales strategies based on data-driven insights to maximize sell-through rates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with channel partners on requirements for data collection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain open channels of communication with key stakeholders, including resellers, distributors, and strategic partners, ensuring alignment, and understanding across the board.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain comprehensive weekly and quarterly reports and dashboards that provide a comprehensive view of channel sales performance, including pipeline management, billings, sell-through, linearity reporting and other vital KPI reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Articulate insights and actionable recommendations to senior management, ensuring clarity and fostering data-driven decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in collaboration with resellers, distributors, and strategic partners to ensure systems and processes are aligned for scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster strong relationships with these partners to drive mutual growth and streamline operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in finance, business, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in channel sales operations, forecasting and data analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in data analysis tools and software (e.g., Excel, SQL, data visualization tools).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage through ambiguity and develop solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work collaboratively in a cross-functional team environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with the ability to interpret complex data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented with a strategic mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Arizona, Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;ChargePoint is committed to fair and equitable compensation practices.&lt;span class="Apple-converted-space"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;The targeted US salary range for roles at this operating level is $92,250 to $179,250. This range represents base salary and does not reflect equity, benefits or variable pay where applicable. Actual base salaries are based on several factors unique to each candidate, including but not limited to skill set, experience, certifications and specific work location.&lt;span class="Apple-converted-space"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to an inclusive and diverse team. ChargePoint is an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, color, ethnicity, ancestry, national origin, religion, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, disability, veteran status, genetic information, marital status or any legally protected status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If there is a match between your experiences/skills and the Company needs, we will contact you directly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ChargePoint is an equal opportunity employer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Applicants only - Recruiting agencies do not contact.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;With electric vehicles expected to be nearly 30% of new vehicle sales by 2025 and more than 50% by 2040, electric mobility is becoming a reality. ChargePoint (NYSE: CHPT) is at the center of this revolution, powering one of the world’s leading EV charging networks and a comprehensive set of hardware, software and mobile solutions for every charging need across North America and Europe. We bring together drivers, businesses, automakers, policymakers, utilities and other stakeholders to make e-mobility a global reality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Since our founding in 2007, ChargePoint has focused solely on making the transition to electric easy for businesses, fleets and drivers. ChargePoint offers a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to create an all-electric future and a trillion-dollar market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;At ChargePoint, we foster a positive and productive work environment by committing to live our values of Be Courageous, Charge Together, Love our Customers, Operate with Openness, and Relentlessly Pursue Awesome. These values guide how we show up every day, align, and work together to build a brighter future for all of us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Join the team that is building the EV charging industry and make your mark on how people and goods will get everywhere they need to go, in any context, for generations to come.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Discover what it’s like to help build the fueling network of the future - check out our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://www.chargepoint.com/engineering/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://www.chargepoint.com/engineering/" data-sk="tooltip_parent"&gt;Engineering Blog.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the ChargePoint Inside Sales team, sales cycles are born, as well as sales careers.&amp;nbsp; As the first line of communication with prospects, Sales Development Representatives (SDR) have a strong understanding of the sales process, excel at researching leads, starting new relationships, and setting our North America Sales team up for success. &amp;nbsp;You will use phone, email, social media, and other cutting-edge sales tools to innovatively engage with prospective buyers, identify active buying interest and create qualified sales opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have the chance to work on a highly competitive and collaborative team, learn from senior leadership and master your sales skills in a fast-paced environment that fosters continuous learning and professional growth.&amp;nbsp; SDRs who establish high performance will have an opportunity for new challenges and career advancement within inside sales and the potential for future roles in outside sales, channel, marketing, and customer success with a hyper-growth company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in;" type="disc"&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Utilize Salesforce and other best in class sales tools, cold calling, live chat, and email to generate new qualified sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Identify prospect’s needs and suggest appropriate products/services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Build trusting relationships with prospects to qualify leads as sales opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Proactively seek new business opportunities in the market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Set up meetings or calls between (prospective) customers, sales executives, and channel partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Report to sales manager with weekly, monthly, and quarterly results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0in;" type="disc"&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;You are located in the Phoenix metropolitan area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Previous sales experience is preferred but not required. Those interested in a career in sales should apply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;High degree of resiliency, enabling you to bounce back from setbacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Player mindset: you strive to compete, grow, develop, and never back down from a challenge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Unmatched work ethic: anything you don’t know you will make up with hard work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;You are highly coachable and willing to receive and implement feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Desire to grow beyond current role, regardless of function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;A passion for disrupting the traditional automotive industry by helping promote the EV industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="li1"&gt;Minimal travel is expected for this role (less than four trips per year).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor’s degree or equivalent required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;US, Remote&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;ChargePoint is committed to fair and equitable compensation practices.&lt;span class="Apple-converted-space"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;The targeted US salary range for roles at this operating level is $40,500 to $56,500. This range represents base salary and does not reflect equity, benefits or variable pay where applicable. Actual base salaries are based on several factors unique to each candidate, including but not limited to skill set, experience, certifications and specific work location.&lt;span class="Apple-converted-space"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to an inclusive and diverse team. ChargePoint is an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, color, ethnicity, ancestry, national origin, religion, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, disability, veteran status, genetic information, marital status or any legally protected status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If there is a match between your experiences/skills and the Company needs, we will contact you directly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ChargePoint is an equal opportunity employer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Applicants only - Recruiting agencies do not contact.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Wurl, LLC.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wurl is a global streaming network. Our B2B services provide streamers, content companies, and advertisers with a powerful, integrated network to distribute and monetize streaming television reaching hundreds of million of connected televisions in over 50 countries.&amp;nbsp; In 2022 Wurl was acquired by AppLovin (Nasdaq: APP), an industry-leading mobile marketing ad tech company, bringing together the technology and innovation of the mobile and television industries.&amp;nbsp; With the merger, Wurl employees enjoy the best of both worlds: the dynamic environment of a 150+ person start-up and the stability of a high-growth public tech company.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wurl is a fully-remote company that has been recognized for a second year in a row as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://storystudio.sfchronicle.com/2023-top-workplaces/"&gt;Great Place to Work&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp; Wurl invests in providing a culture that fosters passion, drives excellence, and encourages collaboration to drive innovation. We hire the world’s best to build a bunch of cool stuff on an interface fully integrated with their own from streaming, advertising and software technology to continue to help us disrupt the way the world watches television.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Revenue Operations Analyst (Remote):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Business Operations team at Wurl is looking for a Revenue Ops Analyst to join as a key driver of sales enablement and time-to-revenue. The right candidate will work hands on with the sales team to streamline processes, organize the pipeline, manage reporting and analytics, while also managing training for new products and services. This role will be a critical part of the Business Ops team, making sure that management and executive leadership have clear visibility into revenue and performance. This individual will thrive with cross-team collaboration to ensure key departments (such as legal, accounting and marketing) are in sync. The Revenue Ops Analyst will also spearhead any and all efforts to automate workflows and find efficiencies, which may include implementing processes and/or integrating software for the Business Ops and wider Sales team. The ideal candidate will have a broad knowledge of sales enablement practices and analytics, have cross-team problem-solving experience and a solid past in driving revenue growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You'll Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Sales, Finance and Business Operations leadership to establish robust rules of engagement to govern sales processes and eliminate friction between the sales and engineering/product organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with sales&amp;nbsp; leadership to implement scalable, repeatable, data-driven processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate successful implementation and adoption of new processes within the sales organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across the sales, legal and finance teams to ensure customer deal desk agreements translate to sales orders and other customer agreements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across engineering and product to assist sales with RFPs and new business inquiries that require further technical support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist sales enablement with the focus on compressing new hire ramp time, improving overall sales productivity, and ensuring sales process consistency and efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate training sessions for existing staff regarding new product releases and updates to current services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal data teams to ensure data accuracy in Salesforce. This will include but is not limited to managing cross-functional teams to establish consistent definitions to process and interdepartmental information collection and sharing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with members of the Business Operations team to develop dashboards and reports leveraging existing technologies such as Hubspot and Groove to ensure forecasting and reporting efforts are appropriately integrated within the company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS degree (Computer Science, Finance and /or Economics degrees are preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years experience in a Revenue, Sales, Finance or Business Operations role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record in improving workflows and optimizing processes - particularly by utilizing automation to improve sales team functions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience running all aspects of sales enablement including (but not limited to) pipeline growth, leads management and internal sales training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be a proven leader who is able to collaborate and communicate well with employees of all levels - from individual contributors to the executive-level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert communicator both internally and externally with customers and represent the company effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative, strategic, roll up your sleeves/hands-on results oriented leader and team player who thrives on helping others meet their goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to interpret and communicate data effectively with strong analytical skills. Must be well versed in Salesforce as well as Google Sheets, Excel and similar programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please provide a cover letter highlighting your leadership and&amp;nbsp; analytical skills, along with examples of automated processes you have successfully implemented and how you ensured adoption by the wider team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Competitive Salary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Strong Medical, Dental and Vision Benefits, 90% paid by Wurl&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Remote First Policy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Discretionary Time Off, with minimum at 4 weeks of time off&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;12 US Holidays&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;401(k) Matching&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Pre-Tax Savings Plans, HSA &amp;amp; FSA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Carrot and Headspace Subscriptions for Family Planning &amp;amp; Mental Wellness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;OneMedical Subscription for 24/7 Convenient Medical Care&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Paid Maternity and Parental Leave for All Family Additions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Discounted PetPlan&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Easy at Home Access to Covid Testing with EmpowerDX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;$1,000 Work From Home Stipend to Set Up Your Home Office&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Few companies allow you to thrive like you will at Wurl. You will have the opportunity to collaborate with the industry’s brightest minds and most innovative thinkers. You will enjoy ongoing mentorship, team collaboration and you will have a place to grow your career.&amp;nbsp; You will be proud to say you're a part of the company revolutionizing TV.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Wurl provides a competitive total compensation package with a pay-for-performance rewards approach. Total compensation at Wurl is based on a number of factors, including market location and may vary depending on job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. Depending on the position offered, equity, sign-on payments, and other forms of compensation may be provided as part of a total compensation package, in addition to a full range of medical and other benefits.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Discord is your place to talk. Whether you're part of a school club, gaming group, worldwide art community, or just a handful of friends that want to spend time together, over 150 million people across the world use Discord every day to connect, hang out, and talk.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;We are excited to be hiring a Senior Director of Safety Engineering to lead and oversee our Safety Engineering team here at Discord. You will play a vital role in ensuring the safety and well-being of our users. Your days will be spent collaborating with other teams to develop new and innovative safety features, proactively identifying and mitigating potential safety risks and issues, and pushing the organization to be the most effective it can be. The ideal candidate for this role will have prior experience in a Safety related field, in-depth knowledge of large online platforms, frameworks, policies, and procedures. If you are passionate about creating a safe and welcoming environment for hundreds of millions of Discord users and committed to protecting their well-being, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity! You will report to the VP of Engineering.&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4 class="margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb"&gt;What you'll be doing&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul class="list-2wIoMU sizeMedium-3TgKSU weightNormal-sMrqnI lineLarge-2ze3kk"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and oversee the Safety Engineering team, where ensuring the safety and well-being of our users is our top priority. You will provide strategic guidance and technical expertise to the team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Discord’s Legal, Policy, Product, Marketing, ML, and Security teams to drive the development of client safety features, anti-abuse tools, and large data streams.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead interactions with our engineering partners across the company, ensuring Safety is top of mind and is built with privacy in mind.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement strategies to proactively identify and mitigate potential safety risks and issues using machine learning and artificial intelligence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date with industry trends and best practices in online safety, and apply them to enhance our systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a positive and inclusive culture within the Safety Engineering team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h4 class="margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb"&gt;What you should have&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;15+ years in Software Engineering&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in organizational engineering leadership, managing other Engineering Managers or Directors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in a global internet-scale consumer safety engineering or a related field, with a focus on online safety, content moderation, and tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of safety frameworks, policies, and procedures, and the ability to apply them effectively in an large online community setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with both going deep: i.e. architecture reviews, designing roadmaps and content safety strategies, and presenting long term Trust &amp;amp; Safety plans to C-suite, board of directors, and external policy makers as needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership skills and the ability to inspire and guide a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h4 class="margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb"&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul class="list-2wIoMU sizeMedium-3TgKSU weightNormal-sMrqnI lineLarge-2ze3kk"&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Understanding and implementation of machine learning in safety spaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class="p2"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The US base salary range for this full-time position is $342,000 to $376,000 + equity + benefits. Our salary ranges are determined by role and level. Within the range, individual pay is determined by additional factors, including job-related skills, experience, and relevant education or training. Please note that the compensation details listed in US role postings reflect the base salary only, and do not include equity, or benefits.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;h4 class="margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb"&gt;Benefits and Perks&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul class="list-2wIoMU sizeMedium-3TgKSU weightNormal-sMrqnI lineLarge-2ze3kk"&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Comprehensive medical insurance including Health, Dental and Vision (plus up to $20,000 for gender affirmation procedures)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Mental health resources and quarterly wellness stipends&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;14+ paid holidays, 4 weeks of PTO + use-what-you-need sick days&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Paid parental leave (plus fertility, adoption and other family planning benefits)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Flexible long-term work options (remote and hybrid)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Volunteer time off&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;A diverse slate of Employee Resource Groups&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Plus commuter contributions and other perks for office-based employees&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 class="margin-top-40 margin-bottom-8 textH4-3Bngsz headingDefault-2s3GxE sizeLarge-2FUtr2 lineTiny-1v9oiX weightSemiBold-19z6Hb"&gt;About Us&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Discord is a voice, video and text app that helps friends and communities come together to hang out and explore their interests — from artists and activists, to study groups, sneakerheads, plant parents, and more. With 150 million monthly users across 19 million active communities, called servers, Discord has grown to become one of the most popular communications services in the world. Discord was built without selling ads or user data and instead, offers a premium subscription called Nitro that gives users special perks like higher quality streams and fun customizations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;We’re working toward an inclusive world where no one feels like an outsider, where genuine human connection is a click, text chat, or voice call away. A place where everyone can find belonging. Challenging? Heck yes. Rewarding? Double heck yes. It’s a mission that gives us the chance to positively impact millions of people all over the world. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So if this strikes a chord with you, come build belonging with us!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Checkr&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Checkr’s mission is to build a fairer future by designing technology to create opportunities for all. We believe all candidates, regardless of who they are, should have a fair chance to work. Established in 2014 and valued at $5B, Checkr is using technology to bring hiring to the next level. Our People Trust Platform uses machine learning to help thousands of companies modernize their background check process and make hiring safer, more efficient, and more inclusive. Some of our customers include Uber, Instacart, Doordash, Netflix, Compass Group, and Adecco.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;A career with Checkr is an opportunity to work with some of the best and brightest minds, disrupt an industry for a better future, and give otherwise overlooked candidates access to employment. Checkr has been recognized as one of &lt;a href="https://builtin.com/awards/us/2023/best-places-to-work"&gt;BuiltIn's 2023 Best Places to Work in the US&lt;/a&gt; and is a Y Combinator 2023 &lt;a href="https://www.ycombinator.com/blog/yc-top-companies-feb-2023"&gt;Breakthrough Company&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.ycombinator.com/topcompanies/valuation"&gt;Top Company by Valuation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team/role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Partner Operations Manager &lt;/strong&gt;to join our Revenue Operations team to help support our rapidly growing partner ecosystem.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will work with Revenue and Product leadership to influence our partner strategy and identify areas of growth for the company. The ideal candidate isn’t afraid of large data sets, can distill insights, make recommendations based on data, and most importantly - drive action from it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You don’t just look at the numbers but you understand the greater business context behind them. We’re looking for someone who will have a huge impact. Someone with a mindset of driving efficiency and who’s laser-focused on what’s going to drive results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide insights to help answer key questions to optimize our GTM partner performance (both alliance and channel motions).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define standard reporting, set KPIs, monitor performance, and forecast results for business reviews and annual/long-range planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ROI analysis to evaluate new partner deals, the effectiveness of incentive programs, and other partner initiatives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Look at performance by partner across metrics such as revenue, pipe gen, customer acquisition, conversion rates, etc. and identify areas of opportunity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play an integral role in helping shape our partner acquisition and expansion strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Business Development, RevOps, and Sales teams to implement any necessary changes to process or reporting infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in Go-To-Market operations (partner/sales/rev/biz ops).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem solving skills. Comfortable analyzing and visualizing data in Excel/Google Sheets, Salesforce, and BI tools (Looker, Tableau, etc.).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with reporting, modeling, and forecasting business performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A demonstrated ability to work independently and prioritize across multiple complex&amp;nbsp; projects in a fast-paced environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong sense of intellectual curiosity and interest in our partner strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in our tool stack - Looker, Snowflake, Salesforce - or similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate SQL experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting GTM partner operations preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll get&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fast-paced and collaborative environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning and development allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation and opportunity for advancement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;100% medical, dental, and vision coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Up to $25K reimbursement for fertility, adoption, and parental planning services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible PTO policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly wellness stipend, home office stipend&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;One of Checkr’s core values is Transparency. To live by that value, we’ve made the decision to disclose salary ranges in &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;all of our job postings&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;. We use geographic cost of labor as an input to develop ranges for our roles and as such, each location where we hire may have a different range. If this role is remote, we have listed the top to the bottom of the possible range, but we will specify the target range for an exact location when you are selected for a recruiting discussion. For more information on our compensation philosophy, see &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://checkr.com/company/careers"&gt;&lt;em&gt;our website&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The base salary range for this role is&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-sheets-value="{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:3,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:93869.75}" data-sheets-userformat="{&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:12369,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;\&amp;quot;$\&amp;quot;#,##0&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:1},&amp;quot;7&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:[{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;5&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0}},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:3},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;4&amp;quot;:1}]},&amp;quot;9&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;15&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Roboto&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;16&amp;quot;:10}" data-sheets-formula="=R[0]C[1]*0.85"&gt;$93,870&lt;/span&gt; to &lt;span data-sheets-value="{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:3,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:195384.99999999997}" data-sheets-userformat="{&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:12385,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;\&amp;quot;$\&amp;quot;#,##0&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:1},&amp;quot;8&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:[{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;5&amp;quot;:{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0}},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;3&amp;quot;:3},{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;4&amp;quot;:1}]},&amp;quot;9&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;15&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Roboto&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;16&amp;quot;:10}" data-sheets-formula="=R[0]C[-1]*1.15"&gt;$195,385&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equal Employment Opportunities at Checkr&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Checkr is committed to hiring talented and qualified individuals with diverse backgrounds for all of its tech, non-tech, and leadership roles. Checkr believes that the gathering and celebration of unique backgrounds, qualities, and cultures enriches the workplace.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Checkr also welcomes the opportunity to consider qualified applicants with prior arrest or conviction records. Checkr’s commitment to diversity extends to hiring talented individuals in spite of a prior criminal history in accordance with local, state, and/or federal laws, including the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="http://sfgov.org/olse/sites/default/files/Document/FCO%20Art.%2049%20Official%20Notice%20to%20print%202017.pdf"&gt;&lt;em&gt;San Francisco’s Fair Chance Ordinance&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://seamlessai-public.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/Paid+Media/2023-10_Greenhouse_Awards-Banner_CI.webp" alt="" width="600" height="337"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: #0065f2;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Seamless.AI is seeking a talented, proactive, and motivated Senior Sales Operations Analyst who will enable the Account Executive and SDR team to move with speed and deliver results. The Senior Sales Operations Analyst is a member of the broader Revenue Operations team and will act as a business partner to VP of Operations, VP of CSM, and our Chief Revenue Office. This person will report to the Sr. RevOps Manager and work closely with other Sales Operations Analysts to prioritize and drive Sales efficiency. We are looking for a top performer to join our high-growth SaaS company and contribute to our mission to positively impact 1 billion people!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Fci2aBSXgAAJYK2?format=jpg&amp;amp;name=small" alt="" width="296" height="166"&gt;&lt;img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Fbl-PVrWYAA5xdr?format=jpg&amp;amp;name=small" alt="" width="295" height="166"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong style="color: rgb(0, 101, 242);"&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Develop and maintain accuracy of sales dashboards and reports, tailoring them for sales leadership&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Analyze data to help drive leadership to improve sales effectiveness and ROI of both SDR and AE teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Understand list building, outbound sales, inbound sales, and sales operation cycles&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Reviewing capacity, close rate, and performance of sales team data and in turn their commission and quotas&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Administer all systems used by the sales team, including cross-functional collaboration on systems used throughout the organization (e.g. Salesforce, Salesloft)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Support the sales department by answering their operational support questions &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Experience with generating commission reports or software (Spiff)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Manage small-scale sales operations initiatives as a project manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Assist in the audit and assessment of sales pipelines and forecasts and redistribution of leads&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Optimize sales processes for increased efficiency and productivity for both inbound/outbound SDR and AE teams&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: #0065f2;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Skill Set&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in operating in a sales environment without the desire to be a quota-carrying representative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in the Salesforce ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-driven with strong acumen for calculating and analyzing metrics to turn into decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with ambiguity and working through challenges daily&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Energetic team player that excels in working with others to achieve a common goal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent excel and salesforce reporting skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: #0065f2;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education &amp;amp; Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor's degree and/or equivalent years of work experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in sales operation or a related analytical role, with a proven track record of driving results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what our employees think about working at Seamless:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://testimonial.to/employeesuccess/all" target="_blank"&gt;CLICK HERE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="postings-link" href="http://seamless.ai/"&gt;Seamless.AI&lt;/a&gt; has been delivering the world's best sales leads since 2015. Our product is the first real time, B2B search engine helping sales teams maximize revenue, increase sales, and easily acquire their total addressable market using artificial intelligence. We have been recognized as one of Ohio’s fastest growing companies and won 2020 Best Places to Work, LinkedIn’s Top 50 Tech Startups in 2020 and 2022, and Purpose Jobs 2023 Best Workplace Culture and Best Work-life balance. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. Visa Sponsorship is not included in our hiring package. Applicants will need to be authorized to work in the U.S.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Pagoda&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pagoda is shepherding a future where NEAR becomes the blockchain operating system. We believe that re-inventing how software is made and distributed is our greatest opportunity to open economic access to those who are not fully integrated into the global economy. Our products empower people to find opportunity, invent new experiences, and collaborate. Let's build an Open Web world. A world where people control their assets, data, and power of governance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Near.org Core Experience team is looking for an experienced Software Engineer to join our effort to enhance near.org with social, collaborative, and engagement features to evolve the near.org developer network to be the best place to build open source software, decentralized UIs, and decentralized applications on the open web ecosystem.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a productive, pragmatic, empathetic collaborator to join the team. Someone who is excited by challenging technical problems, and driven to build performant UIs and collaborate with Designers and User Researchers to build elegant User Experiences. We take a user experience first approach to everything we build so we expect you to develop an understanding of how what you’re working on affects the usability of our target personas of near.org.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You'll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on a collaborative and globally distributed team of world class experienced engineers, providing an opportunity to learn and grow your technical skill set.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow the minimal processes, like technical roadmaps, OKRs, milestones, regular team meetings;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/orgs/near/projects/80/views/3"&gt;Working in the open&lt;/a&gt; while developing user interfaces on near.org&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in on-call rotations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We're Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to solve all sorts of frontend engineering tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills to convey your ideas, discuss technical challenges with team members, and initiative to participate in healthy debates without ego and with an attitude of succeeding together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creativity to come up with proof of concept from high level design while not knowing all the details;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to effectively deliver and receive constructive feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideally 3+ years experience building interactive production UIs in React&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience integrating with async APIs - data fetching, caching and client-side state management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in Typescript/Javascript and web standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid understanding of CSS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree in a Science, Arts, or relevant field is a must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We'd Love If You Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with a fully remote team and the skills to excel at working in a remote environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open source contributions and previous or continued involvement in open source communities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with design systems and components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using a CSS-in-JS library&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with other crypto or blockchain technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working at a startup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s What Our Interview Process Looks Like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our interviews take place via Zoom and typically consists of the following stages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal Recruiter Call (30 to 45 minutes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet with the Hiring Manager (45 to 60 minutes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Interviews (3 x 60 minutes)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pagoda Values Interview (30 to 45 minutes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please let us know if you require any special requirements for your interview and we’ll do our best to accommodate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base salary range for this role is $148,750- $175,000. This reflects the minimum and maximum range across all US locations. This does not include bonus, incentives, or benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The actual base pay is dependent upon many factors, such as: leveling, relevant skills, and work location. If you are based outside of the US, there are other geographic considerations that may impact your final compensation. Your recruiter can share more about the compensation and benefits applicable to your preferred location during the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Perks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Annual Leave / PTO with an encouraged 20 day per year minimum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Holiday Week: the last week of the year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Wellness Week: the first week of July&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$2,000 Yearly Continued Education Reimbursement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$2,000 Home Office Setup Reimbursement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-working Space Reimbursement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company Retreats (2023 in Spain!) &amp;amp; Team Offsites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mental Health Support and access to licensed therapists through Spill, 100% paid by Pagoda&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Values at Pagoda&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values express our company culture. Learn more on our &lt;a href="https://www.pagoda.co/careers"&gt;careers page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos="3874"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pagoda is an Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) employer and welcomes all qualified applicants. Applicants will receive fair and impartial consideration without regard to race, sex, color, religion, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, genetic data, or other legally protected status.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="logo-container"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="content" class=""&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://seamlessai-public.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/Paid+Media/2023-10_Greenhouse_Awards-Banner_CI.webp" alt="" width="600" height="337"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(0, 101, 242);"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Seamless.AI is looking for a Junior Salesforce Administrator to play a role in managing Seamless.AI's Salesforce system configurations, integrations, automations, data integrity and day to day end user support and reporting for multiple business functions including Sales, Operations, Marketing, Finance, and Senior Leadership. This support includes intake of requirements through development and delivery of requests. The Salesforce Admin will maintain user roles and profiles, security settings, and access settings all while assisting users with best practices and maintaining the overall strategy of Salesforce within our organization. Join us and help share the best sales leads technology to change the lives of sales people around the world!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Fci2aBSXgAAJYK2?format=jpg&amp;amp;name=small" alt="" width="288" height="162"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Fbl-PVrWYAA5xdr?format=jpg&amp;amp;name=small" alt="" width="288" height="162"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(0, 101, 242);"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support all aspects of user and license management including new user setup/deactivation, roles, profiles, permissions, public groups, OWD, sharing rules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Salesforce configuration changes, including (but not limited to): Workflow, Process Builder, Flow, assignment rules, approval processes, fields, page layouts, record types, dynamic layouts, apps, actions, custom settings, mobile administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, run, distribute, and support in-depth dashboards, searches, and operational reports to provide insight into data needs for all team functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee data management to improve Salesforce data quality, implementing deduping rules and automation as needed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve user support tickets, monitoring and improving user adoption&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain technical documentation for Salesforce releases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review upgrades to evaluate the impact on processes, configurations, and customizations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with integrated applications (sales enablement, marketing, lead forms, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute data imports and data migrations, including mapping configurations and writing SOQL queries using Data Loader&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform testing in sandbox environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(0, 101, 242);"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skillset:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embraces change, flexible, and can easily adapt to new requests or business use case challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to analyze complex problems and assess how Salesforce can be utilized to solve them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-directed individual who is a self-starter and has the ability to complete assigned tasks independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong business process and analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team player that demonstrates thinning of solutions and flexible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for continuous improvement and learning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(0, 101, 242);"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Salesforce product knowledge and at least 1 year of Salesforce Administration with hands-on experience with Sales Cloud and Service Clouds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certified Salesforce Administrator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Salesforce CPQ preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lightning Experience Reports &amp;amp; Dashboards Specialist and Process Automation Specialist superbadges is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor's Degree and/or equivalent work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(0, 101, 242);"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary and comprehensive benefits package.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dynamic, innovative, and results driven environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and supportive team atmosphere.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to cutting-edge tools and technologies in the digital space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what our employees think about working at Seamless:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://testimonial.to/employeesuccess/all" target="_blank"&gt;CLICK HERE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="postings-link" href="http://seamless.ai/"&gt;Seamless.AI&lt;/a&gt; has been delivering the world's best sales leads since 2015. Our product is the first real time, B2B search engine helping sales teams maximize revenue, increase sales, and easily acquire their total addressable market using artificial intelligence. We have been recognized as one of Ohio’s fastest growing companies and won 2020 Best Places to Work, LinkedIn’s Top 50 Tech Startups in 2020 and 2022, and Purpose Jobs 2023 Best Workplace Culture and Best Work-life balance. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. Visa Sponsorship is not included in our hiring package. Applicants will need to be authorized to work in the U.S.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unite Us CAM Supervisor is responsible for supporting the Pinellas County Coordinated Access Model (CAM), or Care About Me, by utilizing the Unite Us Platform and other software vendors and offering the support and guidance needed to streamline access to mental health and substance use disorder services. The CAM Supervisor will support the CAM Manager in operating the CAM and ensuring contractual requirements are met by CAM Specialists. CAM specialists are platform experts that have the ability to conduct client needs assessments and assist clients in identifying and scheduling appointments to mental health and/or substance use disorder services to meet their needs. The CAM Supervisor is expected to have this same level of knowledge to effectively support CAM Specialists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unite Us believes that an individual's health journey can start anywhere in the community, and you can help us support both the client's and community partner’s care journey experience.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You'll Do&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the CAM manager in ensuring contractual requirements are met, including&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing guidance for the CAM Specialists on the execution of their role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meeting compliance standards for sensitive service types and sensitive organizations on the platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending meetings as applicable to ensure necessary information is shared with CAM Specialists and action items are followed through&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating ongoing support through the telephony system and other software vendors&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow contractual requirements for CAM clients who may be seeking assistance for mental health and/or substance use disorder services&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support CAM Specialists as needed in conducting short biopsychosocial assessment, LOCUS, and other screenings for clients seeking assistance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support CAM Specialists in connecting clients with the most appropriate services based on their needs, eligibility, and geographic preference by scheduling appointments with providers&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Correspond with service providers to facilitate a seamless experience for clients seeking services when applicable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support CAM Specialists in conducting follow-up with clients and service providers to ensure receipt of services/benefits&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide supportive feedback to community-based-organizations serving Pinellas County resident clients to ensure program standards and metrics are met&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously expand knowledge of community resources, services, and programs to understand community issues and build relationships with other users of the Unite Us platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are a great fit for the role if:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be a Masters prepared clinician or Bachelor’s level degree who has &lt;em&gt;significant experience (5-6 years)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in conducting screenings, assessments, and navigating the behavioral health and substance use disorder landscape as an individual, case manager, social worker, care navigator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledgeable of the Florida behavioral health infrastructure and operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Empathy and passion for helping vulnerable populations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quick learner who is excited to become an expert in new technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to set priorities and work independently while following standard operations procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Friendly and compassionate; comfortable communicating directly with clients in need and community-based organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resourceful and fast-paced; able to conduct quick, exhaustive online research&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bilingual or multilingual a plus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Unite Us Story&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As our co-founders transitioned from military to civilian life, they saw barriers and inefficiencies among their veteran community in trying to navigate the most basic health and social services. Together, they set out to improve that experience for everyone in need through technology that connects people to the care they need, when they need it, in communities across the country. Unite Us has developed an intuitive and seamless technology solution that goes beyond the traditional referral method. We work side-by-side with local organizations, and track data and outcomes to build coordinated care networks that support all aspects of community health. Unite Us is boldly changing the nation’s care delivery system. If you want to do well and do good, join Unite Us– we can build healthier communities together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Environmental Job Requirements and Working Conditions&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This position is remote, U.S. based; &lt;strong&gt;the applicant must reside in Pinellas County or in close proximity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The target pay range for this role is: $66,500-$72,000. This salary range represents our national target range for this role. Some geographic areas may have higher target ranges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This position requires software access level A&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unite Us is committed to building a diverse team and fostering an inclusive culture, and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We embrace and encourage our employees' differences in race, religion, color, national origin, gender, family status, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, veteran status, disability, pregnancy, medical conditions, and other characteristics. If you require assistance in applying for open positions due to a disability please email us at peopleops@uniteus.com to request an accommodation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;#LI-Remote&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Hotel Engine is a Denver-based travel tech company on a mission to radically simplify trip management for businesses. We’re not a cumbersome travel management company, nor an online price aggregator. We’re a powerful network that brings hotels and businesses together. Our members save time, money and effort in managing their lodging programs, and our partners get access to loyal, high-value business travelers. It’s a true win-win. Following a 2021 series B funding round at a $1.3 billion valuation, we achieved remarkable growth in 2023. We expect 2024 to be our best year yet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:259}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Across our organization, we’re powered by exceptional talent. From our large Engineering and Product teams to Sales, Supplier Relations, Member Support, Data, Marketing and Operations, our team is forward-thinking, data-driven and customer-obsessed. We’re also a lot of fun — one of the many reasons we were named a Best Place to Work by Built In Colorado for the past four consecutive years.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:259}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;We value our individuality, and we also understand that together, we thrive. Most importantly, we know we’re not for everyone! Complacency doesn’t live here. We’re focused on finding the right people who are energized by our culture and bring diverse experiences and backgrounds that will help us unlock our full potential. &lt;a href="http://hotelengine.com/careers" target="_blank"&gt;Click here to view our DNA&lt;/a&gt;, and if you like what you see, please read on!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the GTM Business Systems Analyst (BSA) you’ll be a key member of the go-to-market (GTM) systems team, and broader revenue operations department. The BSA will collaborate cross-functionally within the revenue operations department and with stakeholders across the revenue marketing, sales, and client operations departments. This individual will be responsible for documenting business processes and stakeholder requirements, assisting with solution development, and ensuring solutions are properly tested prior to deployment in production environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the prioritization of stakeholder requests and projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with stakeholders to gather requirements, create user stories, build test cases, and effectively ship enhancements/new features/functionality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business requirements into technical requirements and vice versa&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, test, and deploy solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide post-deployment support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and integrate new SaaS applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously learn about new features and releases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with stakeholders on new integrations impacting GTM tech stack applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure proper data collection and data consistency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain data quality, integrity, and cleanliness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we're looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years of Salesforce.com experience, ideally within a SaaS organization, including declarative development experience (e.g., flows, validation rules, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salesforce.com Certified Administrator (strongly preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional Salesforce.com Certifications (preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with GTM tech stack integrated applications (e.g., marketing automation tools, sales enablement tools, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional interpersonal skills w/ability to build strong stakeholder relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience setting and managing stakeholder expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker with strong business acumen&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for solving complex problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in delivering results working cross-functionally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong work ethic with a “get stuff done” mentality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Problem solver, strong attention to detail, extremely organized&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter and quick learner with the ability to work independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible, agile, and adaptable; comfortable wearing multiple hats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to navigate ambiguity, effectively prioritize, and manage multiple projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in a fast pace environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written communication, verbal communication, and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cash Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base salary range for this role is $85,000-$95,000. Final offer amounts are determined by multiple factors, including prior experience, expertise &amp;amp; may vary from the amount above.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="content-conclusion"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Hotel Engine Total Rewards Philosophy |&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt; We recognize that there is more to work than day-to-day responsibilities. Hotel Engine has been recognized on Built-in Colorado’s Best Places to Work list 3 years in a row (2020-2022) for our positive culture and robust growth opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;As a company, we’re also dedicated to giving back to our greater community, and have comprehensive &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.hotelengine.com/social-responsibility/"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="none"&gt;corporate social responsibility programs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt; supporting community, social justice and environmental causes. In addition to a collaborative, high-performing team environment, we’re pleased to offer benefits including:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="11" data-aria-posinset="1" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Competitive base salaries &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;134233279&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="11" data-aria-posinset="2" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Annual performance bonuses&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;134233279&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="11" data-aria-posinset="3" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Stock options for all associates + performance-based stock options &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;134233279&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="11" data-aria-posinset="4" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Insurance benefits including medical coverage (with a plan available at no cost to employees)&amp;nbsp;+&amp;nbsp;100% paid dental and vision insurance &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;134233279&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="11" data-aria-posinset="5" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;401(k) plan with a match&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;134233279&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt; program&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="11" data-aria-posinset="5" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Unlimited PTO + 2 paid days each year to volunteer with your favorite non-profit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;134233279&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext="" data-font="Symbol" data-listid="11" data-aria-posinset="5" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;span data-contrast="auto"&gt;Paid parental leave and family medical leave&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;134233279&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
