&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;With electric vehicles expected to be nearly 30% of new vehicle sales by 2025 and more than 50% by 2040, electric mobility is becoming a reality. ChargePoint (NYSE: CHPT) is at the center of this revolution, powering one of the world’s leading EV charging networks and a comprehensive set of hardware, software and mobile solutions for every charging need across North America and Europe. We bring together drivers, businesses, automakers, policymakers, utilities and other stakeholders to make e-mobility a global reality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Since our founding in 2007, ChargePoint has focused solely on making the transition to electric easy for businesses, fleets and drivers. ChargePoint offers a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to create an all-electric future and a trillion-dollar market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;At ChargePoint, we foster a positive and productive work environment by committing to live our values of Be Courageous, Charge Together, Love our Customers, Operate with Openness, and Relentlessly Pursue Awesome. These values guide how we show up every day, align, and work together to build a brighter future for all of us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Join the team that is building the EV charging industry and make your mark on how people and goods will get everywhere they need to go, in any context, for generations to come.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;Discover what it’s like to help build the fueling network of the future - check out our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="c-link" href="https://www.chargepoint.com/engineering/" target="_blank" data-stringify-link="https://www.chargepoint.com/engineering/" data-sk="tooltip_parent"&gt;Engineering Blog.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports To&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Director, Growth Marketing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly driven Growth Marketing Manager with a successful track record in building and managing an omni-channel lifecycle journey to drive sales opportunities and contribute to pipeline growth. This is a critical role that demands a mix of strategy and execution in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Generation: Develop, implement, and continuously refine the lead generation strategy to attract, nurture, and convert prospects into qualified leads. Identify key channels, tactics, and technologies to drive lead generation success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content Activation: Work with the content team to create consumable and interesting content that aligns to the customer journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Campaign Planning and Execution: Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including Sales, and Marketing, to create and execute targeted lead generation campaigns. This includes email marketing, content marketing, paid media, webinars, paid advertising, and other creative approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Nurturing: Implement effective lead nurturing programs to engage and educate prospects throughout the buyer's journey. Develop automated nurturing workflows to ensure leads are consistently nurtured, increasing their likelihood to convert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytics and Reporting: Establish key performance indicators (KPIs) and regularly analyze the effectiveness of lead generation campaigns. Provide insightful data-driven reports to senior management, highlighting areas of success and opportunities for improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Testing &amp;amp; Experimentation: Leverage data insights and continuously test, measure and optimize campaigns and tactics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insights: Be a strategic thought partner to sales and broader marketing team. Proactively share insights across the organization and ensure cross-functional alignment by proactively keeping everyone in the loop on funnel conversion, improvement ideas, and feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market Research: Stay up to date with industry trends, competitor activities, and emerging lead generation technologies to maintain a competitive edge in the market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7-10+ years of experience in marketing, preferably in growth or lifecycle marketing specifically – B2B experience is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An experimental mindset and an ability to act and adapt based on what the data is telling you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for crafting and optimizing the buyer's journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand the voice and perspectives of multiple personas and ICPs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience collaborating cross-functionally and the ability to juggle many priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Marketo, 6sense, and Asana preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional collaborator and influencer. Must be able to engage with multiple stakeholders and quickly build relationships to accomplish objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are open-minded, curious and a strong problem solver.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are nimble and adaptable when priorities change and continue to see the bigger picture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Campbell, CA or Remote – United States&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;ChargePoint is committed to fair and equitable compensation practices.&lt;span class="Apple-converted-space"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="p1"&gt;The targeted US salary range for roles at this operating level is $63,000 to $144,250. This range represents base salary and does not reflect equity, benefits or variable pay where applicable. Actual base salaries are based on several factors unique to each candidate, including but not limited to skill set, experience, certifications and specific work location.&lt;span class="Apple-converted-space"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to an inclusive and diverse team. ChargePoint is an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on race, color, ethnicity, ancestry, national origin, religion, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, disability, veteran status, genetic information, marital status or any legally protected status.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If there is a match between your experiences/skills and the Company needs, we will contact you directly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ChargePoint is an equal opportunity employer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Applicants only - Recruiting agencies do not contact.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="content-intro"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Strength in Trust&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
